Commentary.Commentary: Debutant, the 16-year-old Naseem Shah is into the attack now.

Day 1 started with Pakistan battling out the first session to remain unscathed with skipper Azhar Ali and Shan Masood adding 75 runs for the first wicket. The second session, not so good for the visitors as the Australians hit back with quick wickets. In the third one, Mohammad Rizwan scored briskly but given out controversially by the third umpire. Asad Shafiq then added useful 84 runs with the help of Yasir Shah before the Aussie seamers bundled the visitors for 240. It is time for Day 2 now. Will the Aussie be able to take a lead with a huge first inning total or will Pakistan be able to spring a surprise with their young and inexperienced pace attack? We will find that out soon. Welcome to our coverage for the same.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Now, what to look for on Day 2? Pakistan's pace attack is a much-talked one with the debutant, the 16-year-old, Naseem Shah, being the talk of the town. They will look to replicate what their counterparts have done with the ball while the hosts would look to score a massive first innings total to take a huge lead. Will the hosts be able to do so or will Pakistan be able to chip in with wickets early on to keep the game in the balance? Join us to find that out at 1000 local (0000 GMT) on 22nd November, 2019. Till then, take care!

Talking about the hosts' bowling, it did not start well. The pacers were either too short or too full and that meant that they could not draw the batters into the shots. Going into Lunch, they would've been a tad disappointed. However, post the Lunch break, the pacers combined to pick quick wickets to push Pakistan on the back foot. From 75/0, Pakistan were reeling at 94/5. The late fight from Shafiq and Yasir kept the bowlers at bay for a while. Things changed as soon as Starc got the second new cherry in his hand. He along with Cummins combined together to close the Pakistani innings.

Earlier in the day, Pakistan opted to bat first after winning the toss. The openers, skipper Azhar Ali and Shan Masood negated the entire first session. However, they could not convert their starts into big ones and fell in quick succession. Babar Azam got out playing a needless shot early in his innings, leaving the side in a limbo. Mohammad Rizwan and Asad Shafiq then added 49 runs between them to provide some stability. However, a poor call from the third umpire saw Rizwan depart. Shafiq and then Yasir combined together to add 84 runs between them to take Pakistan's total over 200. In the process, Shafiq raked up his 24th Test half ton. But eventually the hosts' pacers had the last laugh as they finished off the things just at the close of the day.

There you go then. The second new ball brought a flurry of wickets and that sees Pakistan getting bundled out for 240. Starc and Cummins took the second new ball and wrecked havoc with it to close down the innings.

OUT! Caught and bowled! There goes the debutant and Australia bundle out Pakistan. A short of a length ball on middle, Naseem hops to defend but the ball takes the leading edge and lobs up in the air towards the bowler. Starc settles under it and pouches it with ease. PAKISTAN ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 240.
Bouncer down the leg side. Naseem looks to pull but misses.

Dropped! Cummins bowls it fullish and wide outside off, inviting for the drive. Khan jr obliges and goes for the drive away from the body. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to Marnus Labuschagne at third slip. He looks to gobble it but fails to catch it.
Finally a ball on the stumps line. It is on a fullish length but Imran blocks it out.
Beaten past the edge once again. Length and on off. Khan jr pokes once again but makes no connection.
Bouncer down the leg side. Imran looks to duck under it but hits on the body.
Australia can heave a sigh of relief. The clock has ticked past 5.20 pm, which means that even if Pakistan get bowled out now, the Aussies will not have to bat tonight.
Another one past the poke of the batsman. This is on a length and closer to the off pole. Imran looks to push off the back foot but is beaten.
Beaten again! Bowl a few on the stumps maybe. A good length ball in the channel outside off. Imran pokes at the ball but misses.

FOUR! Gets his boundary in international cricket with a beautiful shot. Starc misses his yorker and bowls a full toss on middle and leg, Naseem punches the ball through mid on and picks up a boundary.
Full delivery on the pads, Naseem plays the helicopter shot but finds the mid off fielder.
Another bumper on the middle stump line, Naseem looks to play the upper cut but fails to make connection yet again.
WIDE. Short ball way over the head of the batsman, Naseem looks to hook that one but misses it. It is wided.

Hard not to spot this. The Aussie openers are nervous and Warner and Burns are having a small chat. There is a nervous smile on their faces and then a look at the clock. 'Keep ticking', they will be saying. 4 minutes more. If Pakistan manage to hang around till 0720 GMT, Australia will not have to bat tonight, even if the visitors get bowled out, as it takes 10 minutes for the innings changeover.
Yorker around off, Naseem digs it out through point and picks up another couple. Australia won't mind these, as long as this last wicket pair bats till 5.20 pm local.
The batters out there are just swinging their bat at everything out there. Starc bowls another good length delivery outside off, Shah goes for another swing but fails to make any connection to it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Full delivery outside off from Starc, Naseem looks to drive it but misses it altogether.
On a length on middle and leg, Khan jr defends it off the back foot.
BEATEN! Short delivery outside off, Khan jr looks to guide it away but fails to put any bat on it.
EDGED AND FOUR! Lucky boundary for Pakistan! Good length ball outside off, Khan jr looks to swing it away but it goes off the outside edge over the slip cordon and into the fence.

Ooohh... yorker outside off, Naseem guides this past the third slip fielder, to third man, who for a change, is present. There were two on offer and Imran calls his partner but Naseem has his hand up! Probably he does not want to face Cummins... Just a single then.
BEATEN! Another wild heave! Good length ball outside off, Shah looks to play the slog to the off side but misses it completely.
BOUNCER! Excellent one at that! It is aimed at the body of Naseem who attempts to fend at it uncomfortably but fails to do so. There was some noise but don't know from where.
Full toss outside off, Khan jr guides it to third slip.
BOUNCER! This time bowls a snorter over the batsman's head. Imran looks to play the hook but misses it altogether.
Starc attempts another yorker on off, Imran manages to dig it out to the off side.
Good length delivery on off, Khan jr defends it to cover.
BEATEN! That is a wild heave! Good length ball outside off, Imran looks to heave it towards the off side but fails to put any bat on it.
Good length ball swinging into the batsman, Imran looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. No harm done though as the ball rolls towards short leg.
OHH! Cummins bowls another good length ball around off, Imran looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg and he takes a single.
On a length outside off, Imran defends it onto the off side.
Imran Khan jr walks in at number 11. How many balls will he last?

BOWLED! TIMBER! This is excellent bowling from Pat Cummins. Pakistan crumbling yet again. Full delivery on off, swinging in, Shafiq looks to defend it but the ball sneaks past the bat and pad and goes onto hitting the top of middle stump. End of a magnificent innings from Shafiq. He was the only one who looked comfortable at the crease and has given some respect to Pakistan's score.
On a length outside off swinging away a touch, Shafiq shoulders arms to this one
Full delivery outside off, Asad drives it to mid off but refuses to take the single.
Cummins bowls a good length ball on middle, Shafiq plays it back to the bowler.
Who will be Starc's second new-ball partner? Pat Cummins. 19-6-54-2 are his figures so far.

'Hey! Only one man is running!' spots my colleague, Ruwaab. Boy, a lovely delivery on the hat-trick ball but could have well been a team hat-trick. A length ball, around off, Naseem gets across and looks to tuck it to the leg side but the ball swings in, takes the inside edge and goes towards square leg. Now, Naseem comes halfway down the track for the single but Shafiq sends him back. Luckily for the batsman, the fielder is not to the ball when he is halfway down the track. Gets back in time. What an over from Starc.
What a time for the debutant. Naseem Shah walks in to face the hat-trick ball.

OUT! Caught! Two in two for Starc. The Ultra Edge suggests an outside edge which means Starc will be on a hat-trick next ball. A good length ball, closer to the off pole. Shaheen looks to drive away from the body but gets an outside edge. Paine behind the wicket gobbles and celebrates along with the bowler. The umpire though is not interested as he turns down the appeal. Paine thinks and thinks and almost decides against the review. However, Smith from the slip cordon asks him to go for the review. With just 4 seconds left on the clock, he goes for the review. First, Hot Spot. Massive spot on the bat. Here comes the Ultra Edge, a faint tickle has been spotted and Afridi has to walk back for a first-ball duck. Starc on a hat-trick!

Is that another? There was a big noise as the ball went past the bat. Paine is confident but the slip cordon isn't. Paine throws the ball away but with 4 seconds left, takes the review, as Smith tells him to. And voila! Hot Spot shows a mark! Now, now, now, is Smudge ever wrong in reviews? Ajinkya Rahane, 2015 World Cup, any rememberance?
Shaheen Afridi is the new batsman in.

OUT! Timber! No need to appeal for these. What a brilliant yorker this one. The second new ball has done the trick for them. Wonder if even the top order could've done much to that delivery. An inswinging yorker. Shah looks to jam it away but misses. The ball swings in, misses the inside edge, hits the pad and disturbs the stumps. The 84-run stand is broken.

Huge LBW appeal but that looks to be going down the leg side. The umpire says not out as well. A fullish length ball on the pads. Shah looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The appeal has been turned down.
Beaten! A fuller ball and outside off, Shah goes for the drive but misses.
THE SECOND NEW BALL HAS BEEN TAKEN!
Starts with a slightly shortish length ball, Shafiq pushes it towards the leg side and crosses for a run.
Mitchell Starc is back on. 15-4-44-1 are his figures so far.
Almost an outside edge. This one lands around off and turns away as Shah looks to play an expansive drive towards the off side.
Another full toss. Asad this time takes a single as he mistimes his slog for a single towards mid-wicket.
Short and wide outside off, Shafiq blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! This time the poor ball has been dispatched to the fence. Full toss outside off, Shafiq hammers it to the mid-wicket fence.
A long hop this time. Yasir mistimes his pull towards square leg for a single.
He starts with a flatter one on middle, Yasir keeps it out.
Steven Smith is into the attack. Just one more over left before the second new ball is due and that might be the reason to bring Smith in this over.
Loopy delivery on off, Asad plays it to point.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Yasir sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq plays a sweep through square leg for a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Yasir flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq plays a sweep through mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Bowls it down the leg side, Yasir lets it go.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Nice improvisation. Loopy delivery on leg, Shafiq plays a paddle sweep towards fine leg. Pat Cummins chases the ball and tries to pull it back but fails to do it. It races away to the fence.
Floated delivery on middle, Shah comes down the track and lofts it over mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.

Now, a play and a miss! Short and wide outside off. Asad looks to cut but misses.

Smiles all around! Almost four overthrows. Full and outside off, Yasir goes back and punches it towards mid off. The batsmen take a quick single as Pat Cummins gets to the ball and returns the throw. Now, comes the laughter bit.  The throw hits the stumps at the striker's end and deflects away. Steven Smith dives to his right at first slip, slips but manages to stop the ball. Everyone enjoys the joke.

Full and on off, Yasir drives it straight to mid off.

Short and outside off again, Shafiq cuts it towards the off side for a single.
Full and outside off, Asad gets in position and sweeps it wide of the deep square leg fielder for a couple of runs. 200 up for the visitors.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off. Asad cuts it well but can't beat Burns at cover.

Flighted delivery on middle, Yasir defends it out.

Full and on off, Shafiq punches it through mid on for a single.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short and outside off, Shah cuts it square on the off side and takes a single.
Quicker one and turning away. Yasir covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Flighted and around off, Shah taps it onto the ground.

Fuller and on off, Shah drives it to mid off.
On off, Shah taps it left of the silly point fielder.
Loopy ball around off, Shah lunges forward and blocks it out.
Flighted on off, it is blocked away.

Quicker one on the pads, Shafiq tucks it behind square leg for a single to reach to his 24th Test half century. A fighting innings this one from Asad as he saw the batters come in and get out but he kept his end intact. He has got a pretty good support from Shah and will look to score as many as he can.
Short and wide outside off, Shah looks to cut but misses.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted around off, pushed towards cover for a run. 50-run stand is up between the two.
Full toss outside off, Shafiq drives it through the covers. Cummins from long off moves to his left and makes a diving stop there. A couple of runs taken.
Short and wide outside off, Shah taps it through cover-point for a single.
Flighted and fuller just outside off. Yasir goes for the drive but misses.

DRINKS BREAK! Pakistan have managed to recover a bit due to a good stand between Yasir Shah and Asad Shafiq. They both have looked good and kept the hosts at bay. There is still a long way to go and these two would hope to continue the good work. The hosts, on the other hand, would be a touch disappointed as they could not pick up further wickets. Even though they got a lucky wicket of Mohammad Rizwan, the hosts would hope to pick the remaining wickets as quickly as possible.

Another ball on middle, Shah comes forward to defend it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Flighted ball on middle, Asad looks to paddle it away but cannot make proper connection. The ball hits the higher part of the bat and goes behind Paine towards short fine leg for a single. Steven Smith rushes to his left from first slip in anticipation for the catch but could not get there.
Loopy delivery outside off, Yasir lets it go.

Floated ball on middle, Shah defends it out.

Flatter delivery on middle, Asad sweeps it towards deep square leg and takes a couple before the fielder can come and cut it off.

CRICKET UPDATE - Meanwhile, in Mount Maunganui, which is hosting its first ever Test match, we have witnessed a day of attrition. England won the toss, elected to bat, lost just 4 wickets but could manage only 241. Three 50-run stands were seen, but none went on to reach the three-figure mark. Joe Denly's 74 and Ben Stokes' 67 highlighted the day for the English while a disciplined bowling attack can attribute a share of its success to Colin de Grandhomme, who got a couple of scalps.

Short delivery on middle, Shafiq pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Shafiq plays it to point.

Flighted delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.

Head looks fine. He immediately signalled a thumbs up to Paine, as soon as he got hurt and was smiling as well. Just getting that okay from the physio and we are ready to go now.

OUCH! That must have hurt! Flighted ball on off, Yasir gets down on his knees and plays the slog sweep. He times it well but it hits Head at short leg, directly on the grill of the helmet. Very lucky for Travis as that could have been dangerous. Out comes the physio to have the mandatory concussion check.
Silly point comes in for Shah.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq works it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.

Another flat delivery around off, Shafiq comes down the track and looks to work it towards the leg side. However, the ball takes the inside edge, hits the pads and then lobs to the bowler. Catch it, is the call but Lyon is nowhere near it.
Flatter delivery on middle, Shafiq defends it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up on off, Shafiq pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Yasir offers no shot to this one.

Floated delivery outside off, Yasir leaves it alone.

Tossed up delivery on off, Asad defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery outside off, Shafiq cuts it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
Part-time leg spin now as Marnus Labuschagne is introduced into the attack.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted delivery on middle, Yasir comes down the track and gets hit on the pads.
Loopy delivery on middle, Shah defends it out.
Floated delivery on off, Yasir defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Yasir defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Shafiq drives it towards mid off for a single.

Pat Cummins from mid off then looks to cut it off but misfields. The ball goes through him and towards the fence. He gets up and chases the ball down but not before the batters scamper for the third run.
Short and outside off, Asad guides it towards gully where Warner makes a diving stop.
On the stumps line on a length, Asad blocks it nicely off the back foot.
Back of a length ball outside off, Shafiq sways away from it.
Full and outside off this time, Asad drives it firmly but finds mid off.
Full and around off, Asad keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Yasir defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq sweeps it towards square leg. The batsmen take a run.
Floated delivery on middle, Shafiq blocks it well.
Short delivery outside off, Asad cuts it to point.

Tossed up delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide from Starc, Yasir stays on the back foot and then crunches it through point for a boundary. Lyon gave it a long chase but came second.

On the pads, Shah tucks it towards the mid-wicket region for a single.

Just short of a diving Lyon. A back of a length ball on middle, Shah hops to turn this towards the leg side but the ball takes the leading edge and balloons towards the off side. Lyon from point hares at the ball to catch but it lands just short.
Around off and on a length. Yasir comes forward to block.

Inside edge saves Shah there. A full length ball on middle, Shah looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Bowls a bumper, Shafiq ducks under it.

Well-directed bouncer this time! Shafiq does well to duck under it.

Bowls a bumper, Shah does well to duck under it.

Short delivery on middle, Shafiq pulls it through mid-wicket. Head hares after it and makes a sliding stop. When Travis looks to throw, the batsmen can be heard shouting, 'AAJA! AAJA! AAJA!' and they take the third on the throw.
Outside off, Yasir offers no shot to this one.
Bowls a bouncer, Yasir does well to duck under it.

Yasir Shah is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Well, the umpire thinks it's a legal ball and he sends Rizwan packing. That clearly looks like a no ball. A surprising, surprising call from the third umpire. Rizwan will feel hard done by here. Coming to the shot, it was a poor one though. A good length ball outside off, Rizwan pushes at the ball with hard hands but manages only a tickle behind. A straightforward chance for Paine behind the wickets. Now, here is the drama. The on-field umpire is not sure whether the bowler has overstepped, so he sends it upstairs. There are plenty of replays shown and in every one of them, it appears that when the foot lands, the heel is on the line. Nothing is behind. The third umpire, Michael Gough, feels that there is something though. And gives the benefit of doubt to the bowler! Strange, strange call. Normally, the benefit of doubt always goes to a batsman. Well, there is always a first time for things. The 49-run stand is broken and the attacking innings from Rizwan has been cut short.
Rizwan is caught behind but they are checking if the bowler has overstepped. Looks like that way. What does the third umpire think?
Bowls a bumper, Rizwan ducks under it.

Almost onto the timbers! A fullish length ball, very close to the off pole. Rizwan though is confident about his stumps as he lets it go to the keeper.
Josh Hazlewood to bowl from the other end. 16-6-30-2 are his figures so far.
On a good length on off, Shafiq keeps it out.

Good length delivery on middle, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! Poor start to the session for Australia! Cummins dishes out a full ball on the pads, Rizwan will not miss out on these easy pickings as he just flicks it away to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Welcome back for the final session of the day! Mohammad Rizwan and Asad Shafiq make their way out to the middle to resume their innings. Pat Cummins will bowl the first over after the break.
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

A top session for the hosts as they have managed to send half the visitors' side back to the hut. It started with Pat Cummins removing Shan Masood at the start of the second session. Once the first one fell, the wicket procession started with Hazlewood picking a couple of wickets. Babar Azam came in and disappeared in no time, playing a reckless shot. Asad Shafiq and Mohammad Rizwan are amidst a 31-run stand and they would look to keep it going. The hosts, on the other hand, would look to close the innings quickly. Interesting session ahead. Join us for the final session to find out.

FOUR! Hammered away! Enough of blocking from Rizwan as this time he skips down the track to this flighted ball on middle and tonks it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Flighted and on middle, Shafiq comes down the track and turns it towards the square leg region for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Quicker one and just outside off. It bounces extra too as Shafiq looks to defend. Lyon along with a couple of fielders make an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Ultra Edge comes in and confirms no edge there.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On a length on off, Rizwan taps it to point where Nathan Lyon makes a fine stop.

FOUR LEG BYES! Back of a length ball on the body, going down the leg side. Rizwan looks to nudge it towards the fine leg fence but can't put bat on ball. However, the ball hits the hip and races to the fence eventually.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and outside off, Rizwan drives it through the covers and picks a couple before Warner can return the ball back to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan hops and keeps it out.
Pat Cummins is back on. 13-6-21-1 are his figures so far.
Loopy delivery on off, Asad plays it to point.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Shafiq looks to cut but misses it.
Floated delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.

Short delivery outside off, Rizwan cuts it through point. Cummins chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. He throws the ball to Travis Head who throws it to the keeper. The batsmen get three runs.
Tossed up delivery on off, Rizwan defends it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Shafiq comes down the track and drives it through mid on. The batsmen take a run.
Good length delivery on off, Rizwan defends it out.
Bowls a bumper, Rizwan ducks under it.
Full delivery outside off, Rizwan plays it towards covers for a single.
On a good length and outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Full again on leg, Shafiq flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen cross ends.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Full delivery outside off, Shafiq drives it through covers. Matthew Wade slides and tries to pull the ball back but fails to do that. It races away to the fence.
On middle, Rizwan keeps it out. End of a successful over by Lyon.
Flighted around off, pushed towards point.
Full and around middle, driven firmly back to the bowler.
Flighted and around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, Rizwan comes forward to defend it out.
Mohammad Rizwan joins Asad Shafiq in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust. And this time to a spinner. Lyon has a wicket on the very first ball of his new spell. A flighted delivery around off and middle, Ahmed lunges forward to tuck it towards the leg side but the ball takes the inside edge onto the pads. The ball lobs to short leg where Labuschagne pouches it comfortably.
Nathan Lyon back on. Just 4 overs in the first session for him. Can he get one before Tea?
On a good length on leg, Shafiq looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Shafiq plays it to mid off.
Fullish and inviting for the drive. Shafiq is not interested.
Another one in the channel outside off. Asad has no business with it as he leaves it alone.
Fullish length and just outside off, Asad leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on off, Ahmed keeps it out.
FOUR! Shot of the day! Full delivery outside off, Ahmed drives it through covers for a boundary.
A well-directed bouncer this time! Iftikhar does well to duck under it.
Around off and on a good length, Iftikhar comes forward to block.
Shortish length outside off, Ahmed taps it towards gully.
Good fielding on his followthrough there. A slightly fuller ball around middle and off. Iftikhar drives it hard towards Cummins who gets down to save a certain boundary.
On a good length on middle, Shafiq looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.

Length delivery outside off, Ahmed taps it through point. Warner from gully chases the ball and does well to stop it before the ropes. He throws it to Marnus Labuschagne who throws it to the keeper. The batsmen get three runs.
Another bouncer outside off, Iftikhar sways away from it.
Bouncer this time! Iftikhar does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Iftikhar defends it off the front foot.
Beauty to finish the over! In the channel outside off, Shafiq is confident after bagging that boundary earlier in the over. He goes for the expansive drive but is beaten.

Edge there but just short of Warner. A length ball, closer to off pole. Shafiq goes to play at first but then wants to pull his bat back. He though is late in doing so and the ball takes the outside edge and goes to Warner at gully on the bounce.
Full and on off this time, pushed towards point.
FOUR! Superbly punched! Shafiq bags his first boundary. A length ball around off, Shafiq punches it firmly through mid off and it races to the fence.
Full and wide outside off, Shafiq leaves it alone.
Cummins starts with a length ball around off, Asad keeps it out.
Pat Cummins is back on. 11-6-13-1 are his figures so far.
Bowls a bumper, Iftikhar ducks under it.
On a good length and outside off, Ahmed leaves it alone.
Bowls a bouncer, Iftikhar does well to duck under it.
Full delivery outside off, Shafiq drives it through covers. Nathan Lyon chases it and does well to stop it before the ropes. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets.
On a good length and just outside off, Asad shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Shafiq offers no shot to this one.
Fuller and around off, pushed to point.
Bouncer and outside off. Iftikhar sways away easily.
Fuller ball on off, Iftikhar drives it firmly but straight to extra cover.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Iftikhar Ahmed walks in at no. 6.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is not a shot you play when you have just arrived at the crease. Pakistan have lost three quick wickets and they wanted Babar to play a good knock but he has fallen to a poor shot. Full delivery outside off, Azam looks for an expansive drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards first slip where Joe Burns takes a comfortable catch. Suddenly, Pakistan find themselves in a spot of bother.
Good length delivery on off, Babar plays it to covers.
Full delivery on off, Asad drives it to covers.
Length delivery on leg, Azam flicks it towards square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Azam taps it to point.

Drinks! An excellent first half of the second session for the hosts with all the three seamers picking a wicket each. Masood and Ali after doing all the hard work in the first session could not capitalize and are sitting in the pavilion. Haris too fell early and now the good start is looking a bad one. By the way, Babar Azam, the man who had a good couple of warm-up games walks out to the middle now to replace Sohail.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a bowling change from Tim Paine and Australia.  Starc is brought back and immediately does the job for his skipper. Short of a length delivery outside off, Sohail looks to push at it but gets an outside edge. Paine will not make a mistake out of this and pouches a simple catch. Pakistan slip further.
On a good length on off, Haris defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Sohail defends it off the back foot.
Some rest for Cummins as Mitchell Starc returns. 8-3-19-0 are his numbers so far.
Good length delivery on off, Shafiq blocks it off the front foot.
Outside off, Asad offers no shot to this one.
On a good length on middle, Sohail looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat. It goes towards square leg. The batsmen cross ends.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Bowls a bumper, Haris ducks under it.
Length delivery on off, Sohail taps it to point.
Full delivery on middle, Shafiq keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Asad lets it go.
On the off stump line, Shafiq defends it off the front foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Shafiq does well to duck under it.
Length delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on off, Shafiq blocks it off the back foot.
Outside off, Haris lets it go.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Sohail looks to drive but misses it.
Length delivery on middle, Shafiq flicks it towards fine leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Shafiq defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Shafiq defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Shafiq plays it to covers.
On a good length on off, Sohail pushes it to covers.
Bowls a bouncer, Haris does well to duck under it.
On a good length and outside off, Sohail shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls a bouncer, Sohail does well to duck under it.
Good length delivery on off, Sohail defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Sohail plays it to point.
On a length outside off, Shafiq does not fiddle with it and lets it go to the keeper.
Australia have their tail up now! Hazlewood bowls a good length delivery outside off, Asad looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
Full delivery on off, Shafiq pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball around off, Asad blocks it out well.
Asad Shafiq is the next batsman in.

OUT! Caught! The skipper departs now and it is Josh Hazlewood who strikes. A fuller length ball just outside off, Ali looks to defend but once again the ball takes the outside edge and goes to first slip. Joe Burns there gets low and gobbles the ball up just above the turf. Massive wicket this one as Ali was looking solid out in the middle.

Huge appeal for LBW now. Turned down by the umpire. A good length ball just around off, Azhar looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. No reviews from the Australians there once again. So, the appeal was just to put the umpire under pressure there.
Haris Sohail is the new man in.

OUT! A wicket falls at last. Caught at slip! The no. 1 Test bowler in the world, Cummins draws first blood. A shortish length ball, closer to the off pole. It comes into the left-hander. Masood looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to Steven Smith at second slip. He does not make a mistake there. Cummins drew an outside edge on the fourth ball of the over but that went through the slips but not this one. The solid stand is broken.
Now a bouncer on middle but Masood evades it easily.

FOUR! Through the slips! The frustration continues for the Australians. A good length ball outside off, Masood looks to push it towards the off side but gets an outside edge which flies through the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Gets his line and length around off, Masood comes forward to block it out.
Bouncer down the leg side. Good intent but the direction is not right. Shan ducks under it with ease.
Good length ball angled into the left-hander. Masood tucks it towards mid-wicket and looks for a single. The skipper though is not interested and sends him back.
Fuller and outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Good length ball on the pads, Masood tucks it wide of mid on and takes a quick single. Not a great effort from Starc there.

Great effort there from Warner to save a run. A good length ball, closer to the off pole. Ali looks to drive but manages a thick outside edge and goes through point. Warner chases the ball down and then makes a sliding stop. The batters take three before the ball returns to the keeper.
Another ball outside off, Azhar lets it alone once again. There was some away movement after the ball passed the batsman.
Good length ball outside off, Azhar lets it be.

Huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved there. No review from the Australians either. That landed around off and came in just a hint. Ali looks to defend but the ball sneaks through. The replays roll in and show that it hit the thigh pad.
Good length ball around off, Masood keeps it out off the front foot.
The ball hit the gloves of Masood there. And the physio is out in the middle to attend him. He is now ready to get going.

No, not really. Almost a wicket there off the bouncer. A shortish length ball on the body. Shan hops to keep it out but the ball hits his gloves and lobs just wide of Marnus Labuschagne at short leg. He dives to his left to gobble it but the ball lands away from him.
Another bouncer! Shan ducks under it with ease. Not the length which are going to get them wickets.
Fullish length ball outside off, Masood allows it to go to the keeper.
Good length ball just outside off, Shan blocks it off the back foot.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good directed bouncer but Ali ducks under it.
Good length ball closer to the off pole, Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
EDGY FOUR! Slightly shortish length outside off, Ali looks to drive but the ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to the third man fence.
Landed around off, Ali taps it towards point off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on the body, Shan tucks it behind square leg for a single.
In the channel outside off. Ali makes a comfortable leave.
Length ball on middle, Ali goes on the back foot to defend it out.
FOUR! Cracking shot! Good length delivery on middle, Ali drives it wide of the mid on fielder to earn a boundary.
Landed on middle this time, Ali finds mid on to his drive once again.
Fullish and in the channel this time. Ali is not lured into the drive as he lets the ball go to the keeper. Need to be on this length more.
Targeting the stumps, Cummins bowls a fuller length on off, Azhar pushes it towards mid on.
Pat Cummins to bowl from the other end. 6-3-5-0 are his figures so far.
Another bouncer, a well directed one too. Masood ducks under it to avoid.
Fuller and on off, Shan drives well but straight to mid on.
Another shortish length ball on middle, Shan looks to pull but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads.
Bouncer on middle. Masood ducks under it.
Fuller and wide outside off this time. Shan does not fiddle with it and lets it go to the keeper.
Huge appeal for the LBW first up but the umpire turns it down. A full ball on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses. The ball goes towards short fine leg for a leg bye.
We are back for the second session. The Australian players are out in the middle. Shan Masood and Azhar Ali will resume their innings. Josh Hazlewood will start the proceedings after Lunch.
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

The Australians on the other hand, did not do a lot wrong. They kept it tight but did not get much assistance from the surface. Hazlewood was probably the pick of the bowlers in the first session as he troubled the batters a lot more than the rest. However, one thing the Aussies could have done better was bowling a little bit fuller. We may see their lengths change in the next session though. They will come out with the air of breaking this stand as quickly as possible and then look to make further inroads. Join us for what could be another intriguing session in a while.

A hard-fought session but it will surely be Pakistan who will be the happier of the two heading into the break. Just what they would have wanted after electing to bat. The runs have not come at a brisk rate but that is not something they will be bothered about. Both Shan and Azhar have looked really solid. They waited for the bad balls which they did manage to put away and kept out the good ones. The two now have gotten off to starts and would like to make full use of it.
On a length on middle, Masood flicks it to mid-wicket. THAT IS LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Good length delivery on off, Masood defends it out.
Length delivery on middle, Masood flicks it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
On a good length on off, Masood keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Masood defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Masood guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Good pace there! Bends his back on this one and bangs it short and on middle, it skids through. Ali looks to put bat on ball but gets an inside edge onto the body.
The batsman has driven it through mid off.

FOUR! Finds the gap this time and bags a boundary! Outside off and on a length, Azhar plays it late and guides it through backward point and into the fence. 50 up for Pakistan. They have gone about things at a slow pace but this is just the start they would have wanted. Need to keep going though.
Good length and on off, defended.
A bumper now which is once again ducked under with ease.
Another good shot by Azhar but for no runs! Fuller and on middle, Ali strokes it to mid on. Ali should not be frustrated here, he has played some good shots but is unable to find the gap.
Back of a length around off, Shan stays back and guides it to the man at gully. Once again just the one scoring ball from the over.
Another one on a length, Shan watches it closely and keeps it out.
Bowls this one outside off, Masood does not fiddle with it. Good patient batting here by the openers.
Goes back to bowling length and on off, Masood keeps it out.

FOUR! Easy pickings for a batter from Asia! Starc goes for the yorker but ends up bowling a half volley on the pads. Shan works it wide of the fielder at fine leg who runs to his right, dives but fails to stop it.

A short one and on the body, Shan ducks under it. Difficult to see the short ones trouble the batter on this wicket as it is coming off quite slow from the surface. Exactly what you would see on wickets here on Day 1.
Another good shot but can't find the gap! Josh Hazlewood goes full again and on the off pole. Azhar plants his front foot forward and hits it to the man at mid off. So, the stifling continues.
An excellent shot but for no runs! Josh goes fuller this time and on off, Azhar drives it nicely but to extra cover.
Hazlewood goes wide of the crease and angles it into the batter, Ali works it towards mid-wicket.
Well fielded! This is a little too straight. Shan clips it nicely wide of the fielder at mid on who dives and stops it to his right but can't stop the run.
On the fuller side outside off, tempting the batter to go for it. Shan watches it go through to the keeper.
Starts the new over off with a bumper on the body, Shan ducks under it.
Good delivery! Good leave too! This lands on a length and on off, it then angles away. Azhar watches it carefully and lets it go. Another over negotiated with ease by the Pakistan batters.
Bowls one down the leg side, Ali lets it go to the keeper.
A good short one but once again, not a lot of fizz on it. Azhar evades it quite easily.
A yorker at 142.8 KPH but outside off, Azhar jams it out towards covers.
Bangs it short but bounces at a comfortable height for the batter. Azhar hops and nudges it to the man at mid-wicket.
On the fuller side and just outside off, Starc's looking to get the ball to seam back in but no movement on offer. Azhar shoulders arms to this one.

Goes back to bowling a back of a length delivery, the line is a little too straight. Azhar looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. It rolls behind square on the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Gets the length right this time but the line is outside off, Ali shuffles across and makes a leave.
Better! Still needs to be a little more fuller though. On off this time and it is behind a length. Ali stays back and keeps it out.

Back of a length and on off, it is pushed to mid on. Hazlewood is just bowling a tad too short. The lengths he is bowling at the moment, difficult to see those deliveries hit the stumps. He needs to be a touch fuller.
Errs in line this time and bowls it down the leg side, Azhar looks to tickle it fine but misses.
A short one but not with a lot of fizz, Ali ducks under it with ease.
Good length ball around off, Shan gets right behind the line of the ball to push it towards mid off. A maiden for Starc.
Short of a length on middle, Masood tucks it towards mid-wicket and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Good length ball around off and middle this time, Shan pushes it to mid on.
Slightly shortish length and outside off, Masood leaves it alone.
Just short! Length ball on middle pole line, Shan flicks but there is a man at short backward square leg. The ball falls just short of Head there. Almost fell to the trap there, did Masood.
Starc starts with a yorker around off, Shan gets his bat down in time and digs it out.
Mitchell Starc is back on. 4-1-11-0 are his figures so far.
Outside off, Ali leaves this alone. So just the boundary from this over. Overall a testing one by Josh.
A little too straight and on the pads, Ali looks to flick but misses to get hit high on the pads.

FOUR! Top shot! Excellent response from the skipper! Hazlewood goes extremely full, a half volley almost. It is on off. Ali quite confidently plants his front foot forward and creams it through mid off for a boundary. This has been a solid knock from Ali so far, he is keeping the good balls out and managing to score off the bad ones.

Top, top stuff! Excellent cricket all around. Good ball and equally well played. Pushed the batter behind on the last ball and then bowls a yorker on middle. Ali somehow manages to jam it out. He got his bat down right at the end did the Pakistan skipper.

That has taken off from nowhere! Top nut this from him, seems to be an effort ball. Bends his back on this one and lands it on a length and outside off, Ali hangs his bat out but the ball whizzes past the outside edge due to the extra bounce.
Starts nicely! Lands this on a length and around off, Azhar keeps it out nicely.
So just the 4 overs for Lyon and Josh Hazlewood is back into the attack. He kept it tight in his first spell. Can he now provide the breakthrough?
A single from the last ball which means it is not another maiden! Cummins for once, errs in line and lands it on the pads. It is worked wide of mid-wicket and Ali takes a run.
That is a good leave! Cummins goes wide of the crease and lands this outside off, it comes in with the angle but Ali covers his off pole and lets it go through to the keeper.
Length and on off, Ali guides it late towards point. Giving nothing away here is Cummins. He ain't getting any movement but his lines and lengths have been excellent.
Now follows the two short balls up with a fuller one on off, Ali looks to drive but his hands turn and it goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Goes short again, not as short as the last ball but still short. Ali rides on top of the bounce and guides it to point.
A good bumper and on the body, Ali spots it early and ducks under it. Good aggression from Cummins but Ali played it quite comfortably.
Another short ball outside off, Masood this time keeps it out off the back foot again.
Shortish length, turning into the left-hander this one. Masood goes on the back foot to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Flighted and just outside off, Shan comes forward and plays it towards cover.
Flighted and full on middle, Shan blocks it well.
Another fuller ball on the stumps line, Masood defends it out.
Fuller one on middle, Shan blocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Nicely played! This is a length delivery and on off, Ali plays it with soft hands and late, towards gully. A maiden by Cummins.
Third leave in a row! Once again bowls one outside off and on a fuller length. Ali is not interested in going after those.
Goes very full this time and outside off, trying to play with the patience of Azhar, inviting him to play a loose shot. Ali does nothing as such and leaves another delivery.
Good carry for Cummins there! He bowls this one wider outside off, it is slightly ahead of a length. Azhar watches it go through to the keeper who takes it above his head.
Slightly fuller this time and on off, Azhar gets right behind the delivery and keeps it out.
Cummins goes wide of the crease and angles it into the middle pole, Azhar plays it with a straight bat to the man at mid on.
FOUR! Cut away! First boundary for Masood. A shortish length and outside off, Masood goes back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Flatter one outside off, Shan leaves it alone.
Quicker one on middle, Shan makes a solid block.
Floats this one on middle, Masood plays it back to the bowler.
Outside off this time, Shan defends it out.
Lyon continues bowling short too. This is outside off, Shan pushes it towards point off the back foot.
Way outside off, Ali is not going to flirt with these.
Bouncer down the leg side. Azhar ducks under it.
Gets fuller this time. It is just outside off, Ali drives it towards mid off.
Shortish length around off, Ali stays back and taps it to the point fielder.
It is on a length and outside off, Ali covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, an easy leave for the Pakistani skipper. Cummins needs to bowl a bit fuller to make the batter drive.
Another slightly shortish ball outside off from Lyon. Masood blocks it off the back foot.
Another shortish length ball on middle, quicker one too. Masood goes back and defends it out.
On middle this time, slightly short. Masood once again is solid in his defense.
Landed around off, Shan comes forward and blocks it onto the pitch.
Fullish ball on middle, Ali this time nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted ball around off, Ali comes forward and pushes the ball back to Lyon.

Drinks! An excellent hour of play for the visitors. They have managed to withstand the opening burst from the Australian seamers and both the openers are looking good in the middle. The hosts' bowlers were good in patches but have to do a little better in the second half.
Full delivery outside off, Masood drives it wide of mid off and picks up a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Shan pushes it back to mid on.
Bouncer down the leg side from Cummins. Shan Masood ducks under it.
On a length outside off, Masood pushes it to point.
Full delivery outside off, Shan leaves the ball alone.
Short ball on middle, Shan fends at it uncomfortably while jumping. Good short one from Pat Cummins but nicely played in the end.
Loopy ball on middle, Ali defends it back to the bowler. Nice one Gary, says Paine from behind the stumps.
Full delivery on middle, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up ball on middle, Ali defends it off the front foot to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Lyon starts with a floated ball on the leg stump line, Azhar flicks it to deep mid-wicket and picks up a couple before the fielder from deep square leg can cut it off. Good running from these two.

Now then! That's an interesting move, a spinner within the first hour. You do not see that very often here at the 'Gabba but since there has been nothing for the pacers, it is time for some off spin by Nathan Lyon. Will he get any kind of purchase?
Full ball on middle, Masood drives it straight to mid on. Maiden over from Cummins.
Good length ball on off, Shan defends it to cover for nothing.
Another full delivery on off, Masood digs it out to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Shan plays it back to the bowler.
BOUNCER! Cummins bowls this around off, Masood ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, Masood pushes it back to mid on.

The Australian players are wearing black armbands as a tribute to Tony Mann, the man who scored the first Test ton for Australia as a nightwatchman. He passed away battling pancreatic cancer last week.
Full delivery outside off, Ali eases it through covers and picks up a couple before the fielder can cut it off.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Ali pushes it to mid-wicket.
NO BALL! Good length ball on off, Ali shoulders arms to this one. Hazlewood has overstepped and it is called a no ball.
On a length outside off, Ali leaves the ball alone.

OHH! Short delivery outside off, Azhar attempts to defend it but it goes off the outside edge on the bounce towards gully. Ali played it with soft hands and that's why it did not carry to the fielder.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Azhar works it to square leg for nothing.
Full delivery way outside off, Azhar leaves the ball alone.
On a length on off, Masood defends it onto the pitch.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On a length on middle and leg, Masood looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad. No harm done.
Good length ball outside off, Masood shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Ali pushes it to cover and takes a single. Wade hares after it and cleans it up.
Poor ball to start with from Cummins. Bowls it on the pads, Masood works it nicely to fine leg for a single.
First change. Pat Cummins, the no. 1 Test bowler in the world to bowl now.
On a good length and outside off, Ali leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar lets it go.
FOUR! Nice shot. First boundary off the bat. Full delivery on middle, Ali drives it through mid on for a boundary.
On a good length on leg, Ali looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. Tim Paine walks up to his bowler and then decides to not take the DRS.
On a length on leg, Masood looks to flick but gets it off the pads. It goes towards the leg side. The batsmen cross ends. The umpire gives it as a leg bye.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Masood looks to defend but misses it.
On a length on middle and leg, Ali looks to flick it but gets hit on the thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
BOUNCER! It is aimed at the head of Ali who ducks under it.
Full delivery outside off, Masood pushes it to cover and crosses over for a single.
On a length on middle and leg, Shan flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across to clean it up.
BOUNCER! It is outside off, Shan sways away from it.
Fullish delivery on off, Masood pushes it to the off side.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.

BEATEN! Excellent delivery outside off, Azhar looks to drive but the ball goes past the bat towards the keeper. Paine is confident and runs towards the bowler in celebration but Hazlewood is not interested and shakes his head when his skipper asks him whether there was a nick. The umpire then also shakes his head. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is no bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.

Brilliant fielding from Warner! Good length delivery on off, Azhar looks to defend it but the ball hits the outside edge and goes towards third man. David runs from gully and makes an excellent sliding stop to save two runs for his side.
Good length ball on middle, Masood works it to mid-wicket and picks up a quick single.
On a length outside off, Shan lets the ball go to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Masood looks to flick it and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Masood looks to flick it but the ball hits the thigh pad. The ball rolls to short leg.
Good length ball on middle, Ali punches this through mid off and picks up three. Matthew Wade runs after it from mid off and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
Full delivery swinging into the batsman, Ali drives this beautifully straight down the ground. Wade hares after it from mid off and cuts it off. The batters pick up a couple.
Another one back of a length, Ali rocks on his back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Azhar shoulders arms to this one.
On a length outside off, Shan lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Masood pushes it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on middle, Shan ducks under it.
Good length ball in the channel with some inward movement, Masood reads the line and length of the ball and makes a good leave.
On a length on off, Masood pushes it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.
Starc looks for the inswinging yorker but bowls it down the leg side, Ali looks to flick but misses it.
On a good length on middle, Ali defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Azhar offers no shot to this one.
Outside off, Ali lets it go.
On a good length and outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on middle, Ali flicks it through square leg. The Pakistani skipper is off the mark with a couple.
BEATEN! Beautifully bowled by Hazlewood. Bowls it full outside off, Masood attempts to defend it but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the keeper's gloves.

FOUR BYES! Good length ball down the leg side with some late swing on it, Masood tries to flick it but misses. Paine dives to his right but fails to collect it. The ball rolls to the fine leg fence. Paine landed awkwardly on his right shoulder there.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Masood looks to defend but it hits the pads. Hazlewood puts in a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
On a length outside off, Masood covers his stumps and makes another leave.
Full delivery in the channel, Shan leaves the ball alone.
Right on the money is Hazlewood. He bowls it around off, Masood does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to Paine.
Josh Hazlewood will share the new ball from the other end.
Bowls a low full toss on middle, Ali jams it out to mid on. Tight start from Starc.
Full delivery outside off, Ali pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Ali shoulders arms to this one.

OHH! What a ball from Starc! Bowls a full delivery swinging in a little, Azhar looks to push it from within the crease. The ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads. Lucky that he got a bat on it as if he had missed, Ali would have been a goner.
Leg bye! Good length ball on the pads, Masood looks to flick it but it goes off the pads towards short fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
Starts with a full delivery outside off with some late swing on it. Masood lets the ball go to the keeper.

Time for the action! The host players make their way to the middle before they take their respective positions on the field. Pakistan openers, skipper Azhar Ali and Shan Masood are out in the middle too. Mitchell Starc to start the proceedings for the hosts with the ball. Here we go...
PAKISTAN (PLAYING XI) - Azhar Ali (C), Shan Masood, Haris Sohail, Asad Shafiq, Iftikhar Ahmed, Babar Azam, Mohammad Rizwan (WK), Yasir Shah, Shaheen Afridi, Naseem Shah (DEBUT), Imran Khan Jr.
AUSTRALIA (PLAYING XI) - David Warner, Joe Burns, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Travis Head, Matthew Wade, Tim Paine (WK/C), Pat Cummins, Mitchell Starc, Nathan Lyon, Josh Hazlewood.
TOSS - Time for the flip of the coin. Pakistan have won the Toss. THE VISITORS OPT TO BAT FIRST.

It is almost time for the Australian summer to begin. When the Aussie side last wore the baggy green, they made sure that the Urn remained with them after their spirited performance in England. Steven Smith made his return to whites and how. The world no. 1 bowler Pat Cummins has been in terrific form. What does that mean? Well, Pakistan has not won a Test in the country since 1995 and the above sentence will tell you that if they are to win one, they will be up against the likes of Smith and Cummins who will lead the batting and bowling unit of the hosts. The visitors, as always have an exceptional pace attack with a certain 16-year-old Naseem Shah set to make his Test debut. Babar Azam is one of the top batters going around in the world right now and would want to prove that. He will hope for some assistance from others around him in order to tackle Tim Paine's bowlers. Will Pakistan be able to do so or will Australia continue to dominate them at home? We will soon find out. Toss and team updates in a while.

Mantra to Pakistan - Right now, do not look at the scoreboard. Just look at 90 balls remaining. See them off without any damage. The pitch does not have any demons, so batting can still be done effectively. Stay tuned for the third innings...

What different did Australia do as compared to Pakistan? Why did the latter struggle to pick wickets regularly? One can guess the choking part. There was only a brief period when Azhar Ali stifled the run flow on Day 2 but then, allowed easy runs and that helped the scoreboard to move. Compare that to Australia in the second session on Day 1. 15 overs, 10 runs at one stage. Otherwise, not much swing, not much seam movement, not much turn either. Just a bit of bounce. Yasir Shah got 4 wickets but that was because of the batsmen going after him.

Probably, Australia will not be too unhappy with the timing of the last wicket. They have got 17 overs to get 2-3 wickets of Pakistan before the day ends. A proper Australian type batting scorecard with the batters piling on the misery on the bowlers after their own skittled out Pakistan on Day 1. Secretly, Justin Langer will be happy that Smith flopped. Because he would want a point to prove - Australia are not only about Smith. If only, this can happen outside home as well.

580. Australia's score. 340. The lead. Mammoth, in every sense. And this time, no Smith involved. It was Warner, Burns and Labuschagne who pushed Pakistan on the back foot early on while Wade just pummeled the visitors into submission.

OUT! LBW! Not much use of the review. Umpire's call it is, on height and Australia's batting innings ends. Flighted delivery on off, Hazlewood looks to defend but misses it as the ball turns in and gets hit on the pads. The bowler appeals for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. Hazlewood has a long look at his partner and almost as if to suggest that there is a review left, so let's take it, opts for the same. There is nothing on Hot Spot, or Snicko. Ball Tracker shows that it is umpire's call on height, as the ball is clipping the top of leg stump. The original decision will stay as it is. AUSTRALIA ARE ALL OUT FOR 580.

Huge shout and given! Have Pakistan bowled out Australia? Hazlewood has been adjudged LBW but he has taken a review, after a chat with Lyon. Looks plumb. Nothing on the Hot Spot or Snicko while the Ball Tracker shows it to be clipping the top of leg stump. Finally, Pakistan get a chance to bat again.
Tossed up delivery on off, Lyon drives it through covers for a run.
FOUR! Good shot. Floated delivery on middle, Lyon plays a sweep through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lyon flicks it to the leg side.
Play and a miss! Short and outside off, Hazlewood looks to cut but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, Josh keeps it out.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Hazlewood looks to punch but misses it.
On a length on off, Hazlewood plays it to covers.
In the channel around off, Hazlewood looks to block off the back foot but makes no connection.
Short ball on middle, Lyon pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Creamed through mid off. Full and just outside off, Hazlewood slams it left of the mid off fielder.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Yorker on middle, Hazlewood blocks it nicely.
Full again on off too. Lyon pushes it back to the bowler once again. Yasir misfields and allows a single through mid off.
On off, Lyon keeps it out.
Full and straight on off, Lyon pushes it back to the bowler.
Another bouncer and on middle and leg. Lyon this time hooks towards deep square leg for a run.
Bouncer down the leg side. Lyon looks to pull but misses.
Good length ball on off, Hazlewood looks to defend but manages it towards square leg off the inner half of the bat for a single.
Josh Hazlewood is the last man in.

OUT! Caught! Pat Cummins goes now and Imran gets his first wicket of the game. Fourth catch for Rizwan behind the wickets. A fullish ball outside off, Cummins goes for the expansive drive away from his body. He manages an outside edge which goes behind. Rizwan gets down and snaffles it inches above the ground.
Another length ball, closer to the off pole line, Cummins taps it towards cover.
Good length ball around off, pushed towards point off the back foot.
Imran Khan jr is back on. 22-3-70-0 are his figures so far.
Outside off, Lyon shoulders arms to this one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
BEATEN! Tossed up delivery outside off, Lyon looks to defend but misses it.
Floated delivery on off, Lyon keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lyon defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, Lyon guides it towards third man for a boundary.
On a good length on off, Cummins defends it off the back foot.
Bowls a bumper, Cummins does well to duck under it.
Full delivery outside off, Cummins drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
On a length on middle, Lyon flicks it through square leg for a single.
On a good length on off, Lyon defends it out.
Length delivery on leg, Cummins flicks it towards fine leg. The batsmen take a run.
Nathan Lyon is the new batsman in.

OUT! LBW! Yasir has his third. Brilliant bowling. He pitches it on middle and tossed it up nicely. Starc looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. The appeal follows and umpire raises the finger instantly. Starc reviews after a brief chat with Cummins. Here comes the replay, Hot Spot shows no bat. No deflection on the Snicko. Now, the Ball Tracker, pitching in line and going on to hit the middle and leg pole. Starc has to go. He takes a review along with him. No declaration though.

Review Time! Mitchell Starc has been given out LBW. He after a brief chat has opted to review it. No bat there confirms, Ultra Edge and Snicko. Here comes the Ball Tracker, three Reds it is. So Australia lose a review and Starc.
The batsman has nudged the ball fine down the leg side. They manage to come back for the second.

FOUR BYES! That's gone through everyone. Pitches on middle. Starc looks to defend but the ball goes through his defense and over the stumps. Rizwan fails to collect too and it races to the fine leg fence.
Tossed up delivery on off, Cummins drives it through covers. The batsmen get three runs. Good running between the wickets.
Floated delivery on off, Starc cuts it through point. The batsmen get three runs.
Flighted delivery on off, Cummins drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
Full delivery on middle, Starc plays it back towards the bowler.
On a good length on off, Starc defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball outside off, Starc lets it be.
Yorker around off, Starc digs it out.
Mitchell Starc is the next batsman in.

OUT! Caught! Hearbreak for Marnus in front of the home crowd. A soft dismissal this one but what a fantastic innings. The crowd gets up and applauds the brilliant innings. Labuschagne raises his bat as he trudges off the ground. Full ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to guide it to the third man fence, in search of quick runs. He reached out to play but manages to guide it straight to Azam at gully who makes no mistake. He stands still at the crease thinking what has he done as the umpire check for the front foot no ball. The front foot is fine and Labuschagne has to walk back.
Shortish length ball outside off, Marnus looks to pull but he nowhere near the ball. Misses it completely.
Tossed up ball on middle, Pat comes forward and defends it out.
On middle, Cummins pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter one outside off, Cummins guides it towards short third man.
Full and on off, Labuschagne looks to whip on the leg side but ends up slicing it towards long off uppishly. A single taken.
Quicker one on off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Cummins drives it nicely but straight to mid off.
Pat Cummins is the new man in.

OUT! Caught! The skipper departs now! Shortish length ball on middle, Paine looks to pull but the ball takes the under edge and then hits the pads. It lobs towards third slip where Asad Shafiq takes the simplest of catches.
Full and on the pads, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus lofts this one over the mid off fielder to pick a couple. Did not time that well but good enough to scamper back for the second.
Another yorker outside off. ML this time jams it out towards first slip.
Yorker outside off. Marnus looks to dig out but misses it.
Full and on the pads, Paine dead bats it to the left of the short leg fielder.
Big turn but wide outside off. Paine lets it be.
Quicker ball on middle, Paine keeps it out.
On off, pushed towards cover by Paine.
Shortish ball outside off, Marnus this time taps it to long on and takes a run.
Flighted around off, Marnus pushes it back to the bowler.
Yasir Shah to bowl from the other end. 43-1-180-2 are his figures so far.
Good length ball outside off, Marnus comes across the off stump and tucks it right of mid on to take a single.
Short and outside off, Labuschagne cuts but finds gully on the bounce.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries now. This one is even better. Another fuller ball on middle, Marnus flicks it brilliantly to the deep mid-wicket fence once again. Brilliant batting. The lead is 300 now.
FOUR! Pierced the gap superbly. Full ball on middle, he flicks it between mid-wicket and mid on. The ball races to the fence.
Full delivery outside off, Marnus looks to defend but misses it.

We are back for the final session. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. Marnus Labuschagne and Tim Paine will resume their innings for Australia. Shaheen Afridi will start the proceedings for the final session.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

The Australian domination in the game continues. If it was David Warner on Day 2, it has to be Marnus Labuschagne on the second day. He  is unbeaten on 171 runs along with skipper Tim Paine. Marnus is looking strong out in the middle and has already gone past 150-run mark. After the wicket of Smith, he along with Wade added 110 runs with the former raking up a well made half ton before getting out to Haris Sohail. Now, with 2 days and a session left, what will the Aussies be thinking? Maybe a double ton for Labuschagne and then the declaration? Or will they bat little longer to bat Pakistan completely out of the game. Pakistani bowlers, well, they have been on the field for 146 overs and they would be hoping for the declaration to come as soon as possible. Interesting to see what tactics Australia come out to bat with in the final session. Be back for that post this mini-break.
Floated delivery on off, Paine defends it off the back foot. TEA ON DAY 3!
Loopy delivery on middle, Paine defends it off the back foot.

Huge appeal for leg before wicket but the umpire shows no interest there. Flighted fuller ball on middle, Marnus looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits his front pad. Iftikhar makes a loud appeal along with the keeper but the umpire says not out. Pakistan skipper Azhar, keeper Rizwan and the bowler converge together and then eventually decide against taking the DRS.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.

FOUR! Tossed up delivery on leg, Paine looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It goes towards fine leg for a boundary.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Marnus. And if the last one was use of power this one is a delicate touch. Quicker ball and outside off. Labuschagne waits on the back foot and guides it to the third man fence.
FOUR! Good batting from Marnus. Flighted delivery on middle, Labuschagne comes down the track and lofts it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

On the pads, turned towards square leg.
On middle, Labuschagne defends it off the back foot.

On the pads, Paine nudges it towards square leg and takes a run

Flighted delivery on off, Paine keeps it out.
Iftikhar Ahmed is back into the attack, just ahead of Tea break. 10-0-46-0 are his figures so far.

Around off and slightly shortish length. Marnus taps it towards the slip cordon with soft hands.

OUT! Caught! Excellent take from Rizwan behind the wicket and Sohail has his second. Not the ball you get wickets but Rizwan grabs it nicely there. The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another ball on the stumps line, Head keeps it out.
On off, Head comes forward and defends it solidly.
Short and outside off, Labuschagne cuts it towards deep point for a run.
Good length ball on the pads, Labuschagne turns it towards the leg side for a single.

Full and on middle this one. Head drives it firmly but straight to mid on.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a single by Marnus.
Shortish length ball, angled into the batter. Marnus stands tall and blocks it away.

Full and on the pads, nudged towards square leg.

Driven through mid on by the batsman. They pick up a single.

Excellent running! And that takes Pakistan's total over 500. On the pads, Marnus turns it towards square leg and takes a quick couple.
Flighted outside off, pushed back to the bowler.

150 up for Labuschagne. He is playing a gem of an innings here. He gets there by tapping the short ball towards point for a single.

Excellent effort from the keeper there. He ran all the way from his position to the third man fence. A flighted fuller ball just outside off, Head looks to drive but the ball takes the outside edge and races towards the third man fence.
Tossed up delivery on off, Head plays it back towards the bowler.
Fullish and on off, Head comes forward and blocks it towards cover.
Fullish and on off, Head comes forward and blocks it towards cover.
Full and on the pads, Head flicks it towards square leg.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off, Head stays on the back foot and punches it through cover-point to bag his first boundary of the inning.
Quicker one outside off, it is left alone.
Short ball on middle, Head pulls it towards deep mid-wicket and picks a couple.
Floated delivery on middle, Head flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on off, Travis defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Tossed up outside off, Head looks to drive but gets an outside edge. It goes towards third man for a boundary.
Flighted delivery on middle, Head flicks it to the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Head pushes it to mid on.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus guides it towards short third man. The batsmen take a single.
Shortish length ball on middle, Marnus turns it towards square leg and takes a single.

Floated delivery on middle, Head flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! Floated delivery on off, Marnus lofts it over covers but it lands safely in no man's land. The batsmen take a run.

Tossed up outside off, Labuschagne offers no shot to this one.

OUT! Wade departs! A wicket out of nowhere. Wade was in search of quick runs. He once again tries using his feet there. Sohail judged that nicely and dropped his length just short. Wade then looks to guide it towards third man. He gets a faint outside edge which goes behind. Rizwan in his first attempt misses out but eventually manages to hold on in the second attempt. The stand is broken. Wade walks back with shake of his head. But a nice innings nonetheless from the left-hander.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Shortish length just outside off, Marnus taps is onto the pitch on the off side.
Full delivery on middle, Labuschagne drives it back towards the bowler.

Full delivery outside off, Wade pushes it towards covers and takes a quick single. The fielder throws it towards Wade at the non-striker's end but the throw finds the left hand of Wade. Wade looks in pain there as he removes his gloves and checks his hand. Probably the fielder apologizes and Wade accepts the apology there with a thumbs up.

DRINKS BREAK! Solid first hour of the second session for Australia as Labuschagne and Wade have continued surging the lead. On the other hand, Pakistan are in search of quick wickets. Can they get a few before Tea? Interesting hour of the second session ahead.
Floated delivery on middle, Wade plays a reverse sweep towards third man for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Wade flicks it to mid-wicket.

Beaten! Rare loose shot from Labuschagne. Fullish length ball just outside off, inviting the drive. Labuschagne obliges and drives but fails to put any bat on ball.

Yasir Shah is back on. 38-1-145-2 are his figures so far. He has bowled really well than his bowling figures suggest. Right now, he has got field protections in the deep. Allowing easy singles may not help though. Let's see how he bowls here.
This one is full on off, Marnus drives it straight to cover this time.
Fullish ball on middle, driven nicely but straight to mid on.

Fifty for Matthew Wade! His 5th half ton in Tests. He gets there by tucking this good length ball on middle towards mid-wicket for a single. He will look to convert this into a big one to help Australia take a massive lead.

Now, Afridi at deep backward square leg anticipates incorrectly and runs to his left but the ball lands on the turf and spins away, to his right. So Shaheen has to put sudden brakes then run in the opposite direction which helps the batters steam an extra run. Cannot blame the young man entirely. It is his first tour to Australia and it does take time to get used to large grounds. Kamran Akmal would have been a helpful here as he would have shouted - 'Ghoomegi!'.

We are back for the second session. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. Marnus Labuschagne and Matthew Wade will resume the innings for Australia. Haris Sohail will start the proceedings after Lunch.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

Another brilliant session for the Australians which puts them in a brilliant position in the game. They have swelled their lead to 155 runs already and are still going strong. Courtesy a brilliant maiden Test ton from Marnus Labuschagne. Wade joined Marnus after the wicket of Smith and has added 37 runs quickly. As far as Pakistan bowling is concerned, they kept Warner silent in the first hour of the session. Naseem and Yasir were the two bowlers who got wickets this morning. Naseem looked threatening and removed Warner with a vicious bouncer. Smith showed us that he is a human too as he fell cheaply to Yasir Shah. Now, while Pakistan have managed to get a couple of wickets in the session, they will have to get a few more wickets as quickly as possible in the afternoon session. Will they be able to do so or will Labuschagne and Wade put on another big stand to keep the lead swelling further? Join us for the afternoon session to find out.
