We are ready to begin Day 3 as David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne walk out to the middle. The Pakistan players are taking their respective positions on the field. Imran Khan jr will start the proceedings for Day 3.

It was all about Australian batting on Day 2. David Warner and Joe Burns combined to put on a massive 222-run opening stand. While Burns missed out on a ton, David Warner completed one and remained unbeaten on 151 runs. He has Marnus Labuschagne for the company when he resumes his innings in a while. Pakistani bowlers looked haywire on the entire second day and will have to put a spirited performance to pull their side back in the game. To do so, they need to bundle the Aussies out as quickly as possible and keep the deficit to the minimum. Will they be able to do so or will the hosts' batters pile on their misery for the bowlers? We will have all the answers soon. Welcome to our coverage of Day 3.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Now, what will be the total Australia will be having on their mind when they come to bat on Day 3? They would want to bat the visitor's out of the game by taking a massive total. Will they be able to pile on the runs or will Pakistani bowlers be able to get quick wickets to stop the hosts taking a massive lead? We will find that out on 23rd November, 2019. Join us at 1000 local (0000 GMT). Till then, cheers!

Pakistani bowlers did not look threatening entire day. The debutant, Naseem Shah bowled with a lot of pace but could not stick to perfect line and length. He would've had Warner his first Test wicket but that was not the case. Had he not overstepped, things might have been a little different for them. While Yasir had a wicket to his name, he too could not trouble the Aussie openers and later Marnus Labuschagne. They toiled hard but could not deliver the final punches.

The day started with both David Warner and Joe Burns starting positively and went to Lunch unscathed. They returned after the break and continued piling the runs. Warner got to his 22nd Test ton during the massive stand with Joe Burns. He got lucky once just after the Lunch when Naseem had him caught behind. However, he had overstepped and Warner did not miss out on pouncing the opportunity. Burns fell three short of a well-deserved ton, becoming the first and only victim of the day. Labuschagne joined Warner in the middle and brought up his fifty.

End of a dominating day for the hosts. Australia lead by 72 runs. David Warner and Marnus Labuschagne go to stumps with a solid 90-run stand. Warner could've been back to the pavilion during the penultimate over of the day but luck was with him as even after the ball kissed the stumps, bails did not dislodge and he will come back tomorrow too, along with Labuschagne.

Not out says the umpire there but Rizwan feels that he heard something and insists his skipper for the referral. Nothing comes out of it as the replays roll in and confirm the same. The Ultra Edge shows no bat and Snicko confirms no tickle of the bat. Pakistan lose one of their review.
An appeal for caught behind taken upstairs. Looked like a late call from the keeper. But he seemed confident and that made the skipper go for the DRS.
Short and outside off, Marnus cuts it to deep cover for a single.
On off, Warner this time eases a single through mid on.
Full toss on middle, Marnus flicks it to the long fielder for a single.
Flighted, fuller and outside off, Warner drives but straight to the cover fielder.
Around off, Warner keeps it out.
Slightly shortish length, on the stumps line, Marnus taps it through point for a run.
Flatter and on middle, turned towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and outside off this one. Marnus cuts it wide of the deep cover fielder to pick a couple.
Short and wide outside off, Marnus cuts it to deep point for a single.
Full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On the pads, Warner works it towards mid on for a single.
Flatter ball on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Full and on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Marnus plays it to mid on.
Full and outside off, Marnus sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, it is defended.
Fuller on middle, it is defended by Marnus by coming forward.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Short ball outside off, Warner works it through point for a single.
Fuller and on the pads, Warner looks to flick dancing down the track but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball goes towards slip.
Shortish ball on off, Labuschagne cuts but finds the fielder.
Flighted and around off, Labuschagne comes forward to defend it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Low full toss on middle, Labuschagne slams it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted ball around off, Labuschagne looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards point.
Beaten! Quicker one outside off, Marnus pushes at it to get beaten.
Short and on middle, Marnus pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Flatter one on the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
On the pads, Marnus comes forward and defends it back to the bowler.
On off, Labuschagne defends it nicely.
Flatter one on middle, Labuschagne stays back and blocks.
Flighted around off, Marnus comes forward and defends it out.
Full and on middle, Warner pushes it to mid on for nothing.
On the pads, turned towards mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Beaten! Shortish length ball outside off, Labuschagne looks to cut but fails to put any bat on ball.
Flighted ball on off, Marnus blocks it out.
Haris Sohail is into the attack.

Huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is not moved. Flighted ball around off, Warner comes forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. Yasir along with the keeper makes loud appeal but the umpire does not agree with him. The skipper has a chat and then he decides against taking the review. The Ball Tracker rolls and shows that it would've been umpire's call on hitting the wicket.
Short ball on off, Warner pulls it wide of long on and picks a couple. That did not come from the middle of the bat.
On the pads, Marnus this time turns it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide outside off, Labuschagne rocks on the back foot and crunches the punch through the extra cover region to bag his first boundary.
On off, ML keeps it out.
Flatter ball on middle, Warner directs it towards point for a single.

Drinks Break! After getting to his ton, David Warner is going strong. While he lost his opening partner Joe Burns for 97, Australia have already taken a 5-run lead. As far as visitors are concerned, they need quick wickets to stay in the contest or else the Australians will bat them out of the game. Entralling final hour awaits.
Good length delivery on middle, Marnus defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Labuschagne gets behind the line of the ball to defend it out.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped straight to gully.
Full and on middle, Warner works it towards square leg. Warner took off for the first run to see if he can get the second one. But it was not on the cards.
Full on the pads, ML flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a single.
Fuller and around off, defended.
Full and outside off again, driven nicely but once again straight to mid off.
Play and a miss! A flighted ball outside off, Marnus looks to drive but misses. Rizwan behind the wicket fails to gather that cleanly.
Loopy ball on middle, Labuschagne comes forward and defends it.
Full ball on middle, Marnus flicks but straight to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
On a good length on off, Marnus keeps it out.
Short delivery outside off, Warner cuts it through point. The batsmen take a run. Australia lead by 1 run.
Good length delivery on off, Warner defends it off the front foot.
On a length on middle, Labuschagne flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Short and outside off, Warner cuts it through point for a single.
Good length ball around off, Warner keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, Marnus defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Labuschagne drives it to mid off.
Full delivery on off, Labuschagne keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner comes down the track and plays it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Full delivery on off, Warner drives it to mid off.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery on off, Warner looks to cut but misses it.
Shortish ball around off, Labuschagne hops and keeps it out.

Four running runs. Second time in the day. A short ball on middle, Marnus pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. The mid-wicket fielder hares and pulls the ball before it can reach the fence. It won't matter as both the batters have run four.
Good length ball around off, Labuschagne pushes it towards cover.
Shortish length ball around off, Marnus rides the bounce and defends it easily.
Good length ball around off, Labuschagne defends it out.
Shortish length around off, Warner taps it towards point and takes off for a single. The fielder there scores a direct hit at the striker's end but Marnus is well in.
Naseem Shah is back on. 12-0-47-0 are his figures so far.
On the pads, Warner works it on the leg side to take a single.
Woah! Extra bounce there. And it beats everyone, the batter as well as the keeper. It pitches around off and bounces extra and beats the bat.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short and wide, Labuschagne rocks back on and taps it through point for three.
Flighted and fuller outside off, Labuschagne pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish length ball on middle, Warner goes back and pushes it through point for a single.
Shortish length outside off, Warner pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Down the leg side. Warner looks to flick but misses.
In the channel outside off, Warner lets it go to the keeper.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Warner defends it out.
Short and outside off, Warner punches it nicely to beat the diving extra cover fielder for a couple. The deep cover fielder cuts it off.
Imran Khan jr is back on. 10-1-39-0 are his figures so far.
Full ball on middle, Marnus flicks it towards mid on where the fielder misfields and allows a couple to Labuschagne.
Marnus Labuschagne is the new batsman in.

OUT! Bowled him around his legs. Oh dear! No Test ton for the hometown boy. A loopy ball outside leg. Burns looks to sweep but drags the ball on the stumps off his gloves. He is distraught as he walks back. Deserved a Test ton in front of his home crowd. Pakistan though finally have a wicket. Yasir went round the wicket for this ball and the change of angle worked for him there. The massive 222-run stand is broken.
Flighted outside off, Burns pushes it towards point and looks for a run. Warner though sends him back.
Quicker one and on the pads, Burns works it towards mid-wicket and takes a couple. Three away from a Test ton.
Fuller and outside off, Burns drives it straight to cover.
Short and on the pads, Warner turns it behind square leg and takes a single. Burns wanted the second but Warner sends him back.
Full and on middle, Warner nudges it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Bouncer but down the leg side. Warner ducks under it.
Short and outside off, Burns smacks it through the point region but just a single as there is protection in the deep.
Good length ball around off, Burns gets right behind the line of the ball to defend it out.
Fuller ball on off, Burns drives it straight back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards cover.
On middle, Warner keeps it out.
Shortish length on the stumps line, pushed towards cover.
Full delivery on middle, David drives it back towards the bowler where Yasir Shah tries to stop the ball but it hits his foot and goes towards mid-wicket. No run taken.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Burns drives it through mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on middle, Warner drives it through mid on for a single.
Fullish and just outside off, Burns keeps it out.
Another firm drive but straight to the fielder at cover.
Around off and middle, Burns punches it well but straight to mid on.
Fullish and on the pads, pushed towards mid on.
Around off, Burns keeps it out.
Good length ball around off, Joe taps it towards cover

FOUR! Shout for the catch it but it is wide of the mid off fielder. Flighted ball around off, Warner has his dancing shoes on to time it right of the bowler and just left of the mid off fielder. The ball races to the fence. Australia trail by just 25 runs now.
Flighted and on middle, Burns eases a single to move closer to his century through mid on.
A solid prod forward and defense from Burns to this fuller ball on middle.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller and on off, Warner drives it wide of mid off who makes a tumbling stop but a single is taken as it was wide of him.
Flighted ball on off, Burns taps it almost towards point for a single. A misfield there but no extra runs.
Fullish and on off, Warner blocks it towards mid off and once again makes a loud call to his partner at the other end.
Fullish ball in the channel. Warner covers his stumps, hides his bat and then lets the ball pass to the keeper.
Short and wide outside off, Warner cuts but finds the fielder.
Good length ball just around off, Warner comes on the front foot and blocks.
Shortish length ball on off, Warner turns it towards mid-wicket and scampers back for the second.
Fullish length ball on off, Warner blocks it out.
Fuller ball just outside off, Burns guides it towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flatter one on middle, pushed towards the right of the bowler.
Full and on middle, Warner eases it through mid on for a single.
On off, it is defended.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Warner goes back and cuts it through point to bag a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it towards covers where the fielder misfields and it goes through him. The batters return for the second to bring 200-run stand.
Fullish and on off, Burns comes forward and blocks.
Around off on a length, Burns blocks it out.
In the channel outside off, Burns lets it be.
On the pads, turned towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish and on off, Warner keeps it out. A massive no ball that one.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards cover.

There it is. Century no. 22 for David Warner. Forget about the struggles during the Ashes. The southpaw is back to his best. What a fabulous innings this has been from him. The leaping celebration with the punch of the helmet. The crowd stands and applauds the top innings from Warner. What a moment this is for him. He gets a hug from his opening partner. He is taking his time. Coming to the ball, it is on the pads, Warner easily nudges it towards the square leg region for a single.
On middle, pushed towards mid on. Nice tight stuff from the Pakistan bowlers.
Short and on middle, Warner cuts but straight to point.
Flighted and fuller, Warner comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish ball on off, Burns goes back and taps it through point. The crowd erupts as Warner is back on the strike.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Yasir Shah to bowl from the other end. 13-1-48-0 are his figures so far.
Fuller and outside off, Warner leaves it alone. So the wait goes to the next over.
On middle, Warner taps it onto the pitch on the leg side and shouts a loud no.
Good length ball around, tapped towards point by Warner. The wait for that single continues.
Fullish ball just outside off, Warner drives it firmly but straight to cover.
In the channel outside off, Warner makes another leave.
Good length ball outside off, Warner is in no hurry as he lets it go to the keeper.

We are back for the final session. David Warner is one run away from his century, walks along with Joe Burns to resume their innings for the hosts. Shaheen Afridi will start the proceedings for Pakistan for the final session. Two slips and a gully in place.
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

Australia continue to dominate. Pakistan continue to toil. The duo of Warner and Burns continue to pile on the runs. Warner has got a life as well and is looking too good to continue going big. He would've been sipping a cup of coffee has Naseem Shah not overstepped when he had Warner nicked behind the wicket. After that, apart from that close run out call, Pakistan have not managed to get any opportunity to get the wickets. Will they be able to pull things back in their stride in the final session or will the Aussie continue to dominate? Join for the final session in a while to find out.
Warner has to wait! A good length ball around off, Warner taps it through point and takes the single. He thinks for the second but decides against the second. TEA ON DAY 2.
Good length ball around off, Warner keeps it out. Not looking in any hurry there.

Crunched nicely. Full ball outside off, Burns creams it through cover-point. The ball races towards the fence but the fielder chases it down and saves a single. Warner on strike for the last two balls before Tea.
Shortish length ball on middle, Warner tucks it wide of mid on for a single.
Full and on off, driven straight to mid off.
Short and outside off, Warner pulls but straight to mid on.
Flighted on middle, Burns comes forward and defends it easily.
Full on the pads, flicked towards mid on.
Full and on middle, Warner pushes it towards long on for a single. Just 3 away from his ton.
Quicker one this time, Warner blocks it with ease.
Flatter one on middle, Warner lunges forward and keeps it out.
Flighted on off, David pushes it towards mid off.
On the pads, Warner tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Length delivery on off, David guides it towards third man. The batsmen get two runs.
Short of a length delivery, Burns pulls it towards square leg for a single.
On a good length and outside off, Burns lets it go.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it through mid on for a boundary.
Outside off, Burns shoulders arms to this one.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.
Flatter one on off, pushed towards cover.
Tossed up delivery on off, David defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Burns sweeps it through square leg for a run.

Not Out! That looked out from one of the angle but the benefit of the doubt goes to the batter. The third umpire took a long time in making that decision. Coming to the delivery, a flighted ball it was. Burns turned it towards mid-wicket and went off for the second run, a risky one. Yasir Shah gets to the ball and fires the throw at the non-striker's end. He hits the stumps and the umpire refers it upstairs. Looks safe from one angle but mighty close from another one. Not out says the third umpire and Warner's march towards his century continues.

Run out appeal taken upstairs. Has Warner made it? Babar Azam though asks umpire Illingworth if he is short there and the umpire nods in assertive. Long wait as a couple of angles are being checked. Looks  very tight from one angle. Not out flashes on the giant screen and Warner survives.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Burns flicks it to mid-wicket.
Warner defends this good length delivery off the front foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Warner defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Burns taps it towards point and takes a run.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and just outside off. This time Burns drives well but straight to the cover fielder.
Full and outside off, Warner creams the drive through the covers for a single. He is looking confident as ever at the moment.
Naseem Shah returns. Can he get one in this spell?
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Poor ball down the leg side. Burns sweeps it to the fine leg fence easily. 11 from the over.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flighted ball around off and middle, Joe dances down the track and powers it over cover and into the fence.
Short and wide, Warner cuts it through point to pick a single.
Floated delivery on middle, Burns flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends. Warner wanted the second run but seeing the fielder haring from the deep, he decided against it.
Flighted delivery on leg, Burns flicks it to the leg side.
Tossed up delivery on off, Warner taps it through point for a single.
Iftikhar Ahmed return now. 3-0-11-0 are his numbers so far.
Bouncer down the leg side. Burns ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, Burns drives it straight to mid on.
On a length on middle, Burns pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Full and on off, Warner looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards square leg. A single taken.
Fuller length, just outside off. Asking Warner to play the drive. It goes away after pitching. Warner watches everything as he lets it go to the keeper.
Around off, slightly short. Warner taps it towards point and takes a single.
FOUR! Flighted ball but down the leg side. Warner sweeps it hard towards short fine leg where Shaheen Afridi misfields. The ball goes to the fine leg fence.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Shortish length outside off again, Burns taps it through the covers to take a single. The throw comes from the deep, hits the stumps and then goes to hit the pads of Warner who is inside the crease already.
Flatter on one the pads, Burns nudges it towards fine leg and scampers back for the second run.
Short and outside off, Burns looks to cut but mistimes it towards cover.
Outside off, it is left alone.
FOUR! Short of the day! Full and outside off. Warner creams it through the covers. The ball races to the fence in a jiffy.
Short and outside off, Warner pulls it superbly wide of deep mid-wicket. Yasir Shah there runs to his right and saves a couple with a diving stop.
Full and on middle, pushed towards cover.
Full and outside off, Warner lets it be.
Fuller around off, Burns tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single. 150-run opening stand is up with that run. Punch of gloves between the two.
Flatter one on middle, Warner goes on the back foot to block it out.
On off and middle, Warner keeps it out lunging forward.
Flighted ball on the pads, Warner looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Full on the pads this time, Burns tucks it just wide of the short leg fielder for a single.
Quicker and around off, Burns goes back and pushes it towards cover.
Short and outside off, Burns cuts but finds the point fielder.
Fuller and on off again. Warner looks to drive but gets it off the toe end towards mid off once again.
Fuller and off, Warner strokes it to mid off.
Full and outside off, inviting for the drive. Warner though shows no interest and lets it be.
Full on the pads, Warner flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Beauty! Nice shape away from Imran. Slightly shortish length ball, it pitches on middle and shapes away as Warner pokes at it. Lucky not to get edge on that one.
Landed around off, Warner taps it towards mid off.
Imran Khan jr is into the attack now. 7-1-29-0 are his numbers so far.
FOUR! Nice shot. Flighted delivery on middle, Burns comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Joe defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Burns defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Warner comes down the track and drives it through mid on. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on off, Burns drives it through mid off. The batsmen cross ends.
Flighted delivery on off, Burns plays it to mid off.

Drinks! Australia continue getting strong as both David Warner and Joe Burns are playing well. On the other hand, Pakistan were close in getting a wicket but it was declared a no ball. They are still in search of wickets.
Full and on middle, Burns flicks it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Good length ball just outside off, Warner taps it towards cover and calls for a single. The fielder hares at the ball and throws the ball at the non-striker's end with an underarm throw but he misses. Would not have mattered anyway as Burns was easily in.
Outside off, Warner lets it be.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Brilliant running between the wicket. Good length ball just outside off. Warner taps it through points and scampers back for the second.
Fuller on middle, Warner drives it towards long on for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Flighted and fuller ball this time. Warner skips down the track and just times it sweetly through covers for a boundary. This was a nicely tossed up ball but Warner did well to drive it away. First boundary since lunch.
Full on off, Warner pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off again. Another easy single as Burns taps it through covers.
Short and around off, Warner goes back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Burns plays it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Burns defends it out.
A nice little tribute to the Australian all-rounder and legendary commentator, Richie Benaud by The Richies during the over.
On a good length on off, Burns defends it off the front foot.
Shortish length ball, angled into the batter, Warner works it towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball just outside off, Warner looks to defend it off the back foot but gets an under edge which goes just away from the off pole.
Good length ball on the pads, Burns works it towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Full on middle, Burns pushes it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Bowls it slightly quicker on the middle stump line, Warner works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Slower through the air, and around off, Warner defends it out.
Tossed up on off and middle, Warner takes a big stride forward to defend it out.
Flighted and on off again. Burns strokes it towards long off for an easy single.
Flighted around off, Burns taps it onto the pitch on the off side.
Bouncer and a well directed one too. Warner though sways away nicely.
Shortish length just outside off, Warner taps it towards point.
In the channel outside off, Warner shoulders arms.
Around off this time, Warner makes a solid block towards mid off.
Short and just outside off, Warner looks to cut but ends up tapping it onto the pitch.
Back of a length ball down the leg side. Warner lets it be.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner plays a reverse sweep towards third man. The batsmen cross ends.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Warner drives it through covers. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on off, Burns drives it through point. The batsmen cross ends.
Floated delivery on off, Joe drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery on off, Burns defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Burns plays it to mid off.
Fullish and on off, Burns tucks it towards mid on and keeps strike with a single. A tight over this one.
Around off, Burns pushes it towards cover.
In the corridor of uncertainty. Burns leaves it alone.
Bouncer on middle and leg. Burns ducks under it.
Shortish length, closer to off pole. Burns stands tall and blocks it out.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns pushes it towards cover.
Shaheen Afridi returns. 6-1-22-0 are his figures so far.
Full and on off, Warner drives it well but can't beat diving Azhar Ali at covers.
Fifth half century for Joe Burns in Tests. A full ball around off, he pushes it towards mid off for a single to get to the milestone. He is partnering Warner beautifully from the other end.
Short and wide outside off, Burns cuts it wide of deep cover to pick a couple and move to 49.
Loopy ball around off, Joe keeps it out lunging forward
Flighted and outside off, Warner comes down the track and strokes it towards long off for another single.
Short and just outside off, Burns cuts it through cover for a single.
An easy single to end the over. This is around middle, Burns milks it to long on for a run.
Bouncer outside off, Burns has no problem ducking under it. Naseem not happy with the line as he shows his frustration.
Fullish ball on the pads, Warner turns it towards square leg for a single.
Shortish outside off, Warner this time taps it towards cover off the back foot.
Landed on off and middle, Warner once again pushes it towards mid on.
Shortish length ball on off and middle, Warner tucks it towards mid on
Flighted delivery on off, Joe punches it to the off side.
Tossed up delivery on off, Burns plays it to point.

Floated delivery on off, Joe defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Burns keeps it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Burns plays it to point.
Bowls a bouncer, Warner sways from it at the last moment.
Fullish length outside off, Warner does not fiddle with it.
Short and wide outside off, Warner taps it through cover point and scampers back for the second.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Nicely bowled! A good length ball, closer to off pole. Very close actually but Warner is confident that he is covering his stumps and shoulders arms.
Good length ball on middle, Burns tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Warner blocks it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Burns drives it through covers for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Warner drives it through mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, David keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Warner defends it off the back foot.

The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

NOT OUT! Oh dear, Naseem Shah. What have you done? A wicket on the no ball. Warner gets a life. A good length ball way outside off, Warner chases it away from the body and gets an inside edge which goes behind. Rizwan makes no mistake and Naseem celebrates. A breakthrough finally for Pakistan. Well, no, not really. They are checking for the front foot no ball, so hang on. Naseem has overstepped and by a big margin. The 16-year-old looks dejected as he goes back to his bowling mark. His skipper Azhar Ali gives him pat on the back.
Landed on middle, Burns tucks it wide of the mid on fielder to pick an easy single.
Beaten! A superb ball this time. It lands just outside off and then shapes away as Burns pokes at it with hard hands.
Around off, tapped towards point by Burns.
Full and outside off, Warner this time pushes it wide of mid off for a single.
He starts with a fullish ball just outside off. Warner shoulders arms.
Naseem Shah to bowl from the other end.
Short and outside off, Warner cuts it through point. The batsmen get three runs.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

We are back for the second session. The Pakistan players are out in the middle. David Warner and Joe Burns will resume the innings for Australia. Yasir Shah will start the proceedings for Pakistan after Lunch.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

A perfect session for the visitors on the surface which looks like heaven for batting. Warner and Burns have comfortably raked up a 100-run stand between them. The Pakistani bowlers have not tested them much. While they hardly got any assistance from the surface, they were not consistent with their lines and lengths throughout. Warner has brought up his 31st half ton and looking solid out in the middle. He will look to convert this one into a massive one. Seems like a long and hard day for the Pakistani seamers and spinners. They need quick wickets to get back in the game. Will they be able to do so or the Australian openers will continue piling on the runs? Join for the afternoon session to find out.
Around off, Burns keeps it out to GO TO LUNCH.
Ouch! That would've hurt. A bouncer on middle, this does not bounce as much as Burns accepted. He looks to duck but gets hit on the arm. One ball to go before Lunch.
Bouncer on middle, Burns has no problems ducking under it.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns keeps it out off the back foot.
Around off, Burns defends it out.
Length ball on middle, Burns works it towards deep mid-wicket and picks a couple. The two brings up 100 run stand between them.
On middle, Warner goes back and blocks it out.
Loopy ball on middle, Warner pushes it towards mid on.
Full and on middle, pushed through cover for a single. Easy runs on offer these.
Flighted and on middle, Burns takes a big stride forward to keep it out.
Short and around off, Joe cuts it towards point.
Full and on the pads, Warner tucks it towards mid-wicket and calls for a quick single.
Bouncer on middle, Burns ducks under it.
Fuller length and around off, Warner looks to defend but gets an inside edge. Could've been easily dragged this on the stumps. It goes towards short fine leg for a single.
Shortish length around off, Warner keeps it out.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Landed outside off, Burns taps it towards the off side for another single.

Fifty for David Warner on return in whites at home. Full and outside off, Warner drives it towards cover where the fielder makes a diving stop but cannot prevent Warner from taking the single. His 31st half ton but he would want to convert this into a big one.
Naseem Shah returns. 4-0-19-0 are his figures so far.
Tossed up delivery on leg, Warner flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Floated delivery on off, David keeps it out.
Short ball on middle, Warner pulls but hits Shan Masood at short leg. It was a tough chance for Masood but it will go down as a dropped one.
FOUR! Superbly timed! Full and wide outside off, Warner creams it through the covers to move to 48. Just two away from his half ton.
Fuller and on middle, Warner tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter one on the pads, Warner pushes it towards mid on.
Around off, it is defended.
Outside off, Burns lets it be.
FOUR! No pace on the bouncer on middle. Burns rocks back on the back foot and powers the pull to the deep square leg fence.
Shortish length around off, Burns taps it towards mid off.
Landed around off, Burns defends it out coming forward.
Full and on off and middle, Joe pushes it towards mid on.
On middle, Warner tucks it towards the leg side. Just a single from Yasir's first. A tight over followed by the last over maiden.
Quicker one around off, Warner blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted on middle this time, Warner comes forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Warner comes down the track and pushes it towards cover.
On the pads and a fullish length. Warner taps it towards mid on.
He starts with a short ball outside off. Burns taps it through point for a single.
Finally, a glimpse of their premier spinner as Yasir Shah has been brought into the attack. A slip and a short leg in place.
Outside off, it is left alone. Just the second maiden over of the innings.
Around off, defended towards cover.
Fuller and on off, Warner looks to drive but the ball goes towards mid on off the inner half of the bat
Good directed bouncer! Warner sways away from it.
In the channel outside off, Warner lets it be.
Shortish length outside off, Warner pushes it towards cover.
Quicker one on the pads, Joe tucks it straight to short fine leg.
Short and outside off now. Burns cuts but finds the point fielder.
FOUR! Burns on the charge! Flighted ball on middle, Joe skips down the track and slams it inside out through the covers to earn another boundary.
On middle, Warner pushes it towards long on for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, David defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up delivery on off, Warner keeps it out.
Good length delivery on off, Burns looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length ball just outside off, Burns taps it towards point.
Not good bowling this from Imran. Short and wide outside off. Warner cuts it to deep point for an easy single.
Landed on middle, Warner turns it towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short ball on middle, Burns pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Quicker and shorter one. Burns stays on the back foot to turn it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Tossed up on the stumps line, Burns once again pushes it towards mid on.
On middle, Joe pushes it towards mid on.
Shortish length, Burns taps it towards point.
FOUR! Up and over. Flighted ball around off, Burns skips down the track and lofts it to the long on fence to bag a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Short ball on middle, Warner stays on the back foot and pulls. The ball goes to the long on fence. Did not time it well but good enough to reach to the fence.
Length and around off, Warner pushes it back to the bowler.
Landed on middle, Warner works it towards mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, Imran wants Warner to go for the drive. Warner says, no sorry and shoulders arms.
He starts with a length ball on middle, Warner taps it towards the leg side.
Imran Khan jr is back on. 3-0-19-0 are his figures so far.
Another ball on the stumps line, Burns keeps it out.
On middle, Burns once again comes forward and defends.
Full and off, Burns lunges forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Warner pushes it towards cover where Azam misfields and allows a single.
Around off, it is defended.
Starts with a ball on the pads, Warner nudges it towards the leg side but Masood at short leg is once again sharp in stopping the ball.
Interesting from the Pakistani skipper as instead of giving the ball to the premier bowler, Yasir Shah he has gone for Iftikhar. Interestingly, Lyon came to bowl inside the first hour on Day 1.
Spin for the first time as Iftikhar Ahmed is into the attack. A slip and a short leg in place.
Outside off, Burns lets it be.
FOUR! Hammered! Short and around off, Burns pulls it to the deep square leg region. The ball bounces just inside the rope and goes to the fence.
On the pads, Burns turns it towards square leg to pick an easy couple.
Full and outside off, inviting for the drive. Burns though lets it be.
Shortish length and just outside off, Warner taps it towards gully and crosses for a single.
Another quick single. A fuller ball on off, Burns taps it on the off side and takes off for a quick run.
Shortish length ball around off, it is defended easily by Warner.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Four running runs. Great effort from the two. A overpitched ball outside off, Warner drives it through the covers superbly. The ball races towards the fence but the cover fielder chases it down with a sliding effort. However, Warner and Burns take the fourth run on the throw from the deep.
Length ball around off, Burns taps it towards cover and takes a quick single.
Full again on off, Burns blocks it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Burns defends it out.

Drinks Break! A superb first hour for the visitors as Warner and Burns have added 53 runs without much trouble. The Pakistani bowlers have not been consistent with their lines and lengths. They need to do so to trouble this pair and have the chance of getting more wickets. Naseem, the debutant has cranked up a nice pace and bowled a barrage of bouncers to Warner. The next hour should be an interesting one. Let us see how it pans out.
Naseem has another look at Warner after he bowls a sharp bouncer around off. Warner once again drops his hands and lets it go to the keeper.
Landed around off, Warner is right behind the line of the delivery to defend it out.
This time he sprays further down the leg side. Warner looks to flick but misses.
Another stare from Naseem! Good contest this one. A short of a length ball on middle, Warner does well to evade it.
Bouncer! Warner ducks under it. Naseem has a stare at Warner. Interesting.
Strays on the pads there does Naseem, Warner nudges it towards fine leg and takes two. Aggressive running from him.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Burns looks to defend but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Full and off, Burns gets on the front foot to defend it out.
Full and on off, Burns pushes it towards covers.
No ball! The umpire this time spots it. A good length ball around off, Burns defends it out. A massive no ball.
A short ball on off and middle, Burns ducks under it.
Outside off, Burns is not going after them as he shoulders arms.
On the pads, Warner nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single to bring 50-run stand for the opening wicket. Top start for the hosts.
Outside off, Burns lets it go the keeper.
On middle, tucked towards the leg side. Oh, hello, the replays show that even on this ball, Naseem overstepped.
Another back of a length ball on middle and leg. Burns has no problem ducking under it. The replays show that Naseem has overstepped by a big margin. Poor from the on-field umpire.
Bouncer this time which is way over Burns head.
A single now. Smart batting. Good length ball around off, Warner drops the short on the off side and takes a quick single.

FOUR! Cuts, cuts hard and cuts well. You cannot bowl Warner short and outside off and the youngster needs to learn that quickly. Short and wide outside off, Warner cuts it over point to get a boundary.
Full and outside off, Warner creams the drive through covers. Three more for Warner. The timing is not from the sweetest part of the willow and hence the ball does not reach the fence.
Outside off, Warner does not fiddle with it.

Around off. Warner pushes it towards the left of the bowler and ventures out of the crease. Afridi fields the ball in his followthrough and seeing that Warner returns back. Afridi though fires the throw at the striker's end but no casualty there.
Shaheen bends his back and bowls a bouncer on middle. Warner ducks under it.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
On the pads, Burns turns it towards square leg for a single.
Shaheen Afridi has a change of ends.

Two Byes! Poor effort from the keeper there. A ball in the channel again. Warner lets it be but Rizwan cannot gather it cleanly. The ball goes behind him and the batters take a couple of byes. Pacy over this one from Naseem.
The youngster is generating a lot of pace here. 147 kph, the last one. It is on the stumps line, Warner though is right behind the line of the delivery to defend.
Outside off this one. Warner lets it be.
On the pads this one, Burns nudges it towards fine leg to pick a single.

This one is short and wide outside off. Warner taps it towards point to beat the diving point fielder. Warner gets three more as one of the slip fielder hares at the ball to stop it going to the fence.
Naseem starts with a shortish length ball just outside off, Warner looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid off.
Shortish length ball around off, Burns taps it towards point.

Goes around the wicket but bowls the same delivery. Full and wide outside off. Warner once again drives it through the covers but the timing this time is not as good as the last ball. Azhar Ali chases it down as Warner gets three more.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished. Full and wide outside off. Warner creams this one through the covers to bag his first boundary of the innings.
On the pads this time. Warner tucks it towards deep square leg and gets two more easy runs. Imran bowling too straight.
Fullish ball outside off, Warner punches it through the covers to pick a couple of runs.
Outside off, Warner covers his stumps and lets it be.
Around off, Warner taps it wide of gully to pick a single.
Length ball on middle, Burns tucks it towards square leg to pick an easy single.
On middle this time, Warner tucks it towards mid on.
Full ball on off, Burns pushes it towards mid off.
FOUR LEG BYES! On the pads from Afridi. Burns looks to glance it to the fine leg fence but gets hit on the pads. The ball eventually goes to the fence.
Fuller length ball around off, Warner guides it through gully. The ball races towards the fence but Babar Azam chases it down with a slide. Three runs taken.
Around off, Burns keeps it out.

Good work from the skipper at mid off. A fuller length ball on off, Warner drives it to the right of the bowler. Ali dives to his left and makes a half stop. The ball rolls behind and Warner takes a single.
Beauty! Now bowls a fullish length ball outside off. This pitches around off and moves away. This is inviting Warner for the drive. He does so to get beaten.
In the channel outside off, Warner is not interested as he lets it be.
Good length ball around off, Warner taps it towards covers and looks for a single. Realizes quickly that it could be a risky run so he returns back with a wait, wait call.
Imran starts his second over with a ball on the pads. Burns nudges it behind square leg to cross ends.
On the stumps line, Warner defends it back to the bowler and shouts a loud no for the run.
Good length ball around off, Warner looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball goes towards cover.
Length ball on the pads this time, Burns tucks it wide of the short mid-wicket fielder and takes a run.

EDGY FOUR! Through the vacant area between the slip and gully region. This is a fullish length ball around off, Burns looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and races to the third man fence.
On a length and just outside off, Warner pushes it towards cover and takes a quick single.
Landed on middle, Warner pushes it towards the leg side.
Outside off, Burns makes a leave now.
FOUR! Poor ball and Burns is not going to miss out on these. Short and wide outside off. Burns stays on the back foot and cuts it over the gully region to pick the first boundary of the innings.

Brilliant work from Shan Masood at short leg. A length ball on the pads, Burns looks to work it on the leg side but short leg fielder shows great reflexes to field the ball. Burns though is out of the crease. Masood throws the ball at the stumps but can't score a hit. Had he hit, Burns would've been going back to the pavilion.
Around off, Warner taps it towards cover and takes a run to get off the mark.
Burns and Australia are away. A shortish length on middle this time, Burns pulls well but the ball hits the short leg fielder on his shin pads and rolls towards mid on for a single.

Did that carry? No, just short. A shortish length ball wide outside off, Burns goes after it but manages a little under edge which dies in front of the keeper who comes forward to catch but can't get to it. The bowler doesn't seem to be happy with the effort of the keeper there.
Imran Khan jr to bowl from the other end.
Outside off, Warner lets it be. A maiden to start by Shaheen.
On middle, this is defended off the back foot by Warner. Nice lines and length in the first over by Afridi.
Goes for the inswinging yorker this time. Warner gets his bat down in time to dig it out.
In the channel outside off, Warner this time allows it to pass through to the keeper. Not much movement on the first three deliveries there.
This is on a length and on the pads, Warner tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Shaheen starts with a shortish length ball just outside off, Warner sways away from it.

So! A bit of a dramatic end to what has been a one-sided Test match. Australia get some much needed 60 points to go second in the World Test Championship table. Will the pink ball produce a different result? A better contest at least? Both Australia and Pakistan have a decent record in Day/Night Tests. The second match in Adelaide should be a cracker. Join us on Friday, November 29, 2019 at 2 pm local (0330 GMT). ADIOS! TAKE CARE!

MARNUS LABUSCHAGNE HAS BEEN NAMED THE MAN OF THE MATCH. On his maiden Test century at his home ground, Labuschagne says that it is very special to have everything pan out like that and is happy that he could contribute to the team's winning cause. On the nervous moments before his ton. Marnus admits that it was tough as he was keeping on thinking whether he will get there and believes he was lucky to get there. Adds that it was a big moment for him and his family. On his batting technique and mindset, Labuschagne says that playing in England has helped him and here, in Queensland as well, batting ain't easy, so that made him mentally tough. Is looking forward for the Day/Night Test in Adelaide.

Victorious Australian captain, Tim Paine, says that he is really happy. Especially given the innings victory and maintaining their excellent record at the 'Gabba. On contributions other than Steven Smith, Tim is happy as the team does not want to rely on Smith pretty heavily. Stresses that on a very good wicket, 580 is exactly the score that was expected out of the batsmen. On Warner getting back to form, the skipper says that many left-handers struggle in England but they always believed that Warner will strike form in Australia. On the Warner-Burns partnership, Paine says that he is not sure, as he has not spent too much time with Burns in the dressing room but is happy that whatever it is that keeps the pair ticking, it is great. On Marnus Labuschagne, Paine says that he is a great bloke to have as a mate, always keeping the dressing room in high spirits. Is happy that Labuschagne has realized his true potential. On his bowlers, Paine says that they were good but given the high standards that they have raised for themselves, he would have expected them to clean up Pakistan a bit earlier. But adds that Australia are lucky to have such a pace attack.

Pakistan skipper, Azhar Ali says that all of Pakistan's batsmen are in good nick and Babar showed that once they get a good partnership going, runs were always on offer. Praises the wicket which was very good but rues the missed opportunity in the first innings. On missing Mohammad Abbas, Ali says that it was always hard to leave someone like Abbas but the selection was done based on the performance of the trio in the warm-up match. Ensures that Abbas will always be there for Pakistan and they will come back hard in the second Test. Praises the debutant Naseem for having good temperament for a 16-year old, adjusting to the lengths and lines pretty quickly. On him being given just 4 overs on Saturday, Azhar says that Naseem is fit but the management does not want him to break down, hence they are managing him accordingly.

Now, for the summary of the match. Probably got over when Pakistan slipped from 75/0 to 94/5 on Day 1 and then managed just 240 after electing to bat. From there on, it was very difficult for them to come back and Warner-Burns' 222-run opening stand floored them. Yasir Shah was over the moon when he dismissed Steven Smith for the 7th time in Tests but they forgot that the Ashes had already prepared a substitute for Smudge - Marnus Labuschagne. The home lad played with total control and ensured that his side batted Pakistan out of the Test. Yasir Shah got 4 wickets but the bowling did not look threatening at all. Please stay tuned for the presentation...

First, Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan added 132 for the 6th wicket and that was followed by a 79-run stand between Rizwan and Yasir. Azam scored a fantastic century but Rizwan missed his, while Yasir nearly got Australia batting again. Once again, it was the quartet of New South Wales bowlers as Starc, Cummins, Hazlewood and Lyon took all the 10 wickets. Not that there were any more options. Starc took four in the first innings while Hazlewood got 4 in the second.

Babar Azam, Shan Masood, Mohammad Rizwan and Yasir Shah - The Fantastic Four. They are the ones who kept Pakistan believing that they could fight and could avoid an innings defeat. Because after them, only Afridi managed double figures. Masood and Azam fought hard this morning, delaying Australia's quest for wickets and then the real fightback began.

5 runs. That is what Pakistan fall short of to make Australia bat again. An innings defeat was expected and an innings defeat it is but what an epic fightback. Almost a reminiscent of the 2016 match where Pakistan nearly chased down 490. This time, they were chasing down 340 with the only difference being that the focus was to avoid an innings defeat.

OUT! Caught! No, they will not have to because Imran has holed out. Good length ball on middle, Imran looks to power it over the mid-wicket fence this time but manages only a top edge. Wade from long on comes forward to catch but initially misjudges it. He backtracks and then manages to hold onto the catch over his head. Australia win the first Test by an innings and five runs.

FOUR! What a shot that is! Hits it over the bowler's head. Fullish length just around off, Imran clears his front leg and hammers it over mid on for a boundary. Five more runs and Australia will have to bat again.
Hazlewood tries to bowl the inswinging yorker but ends up missing it and bowling a full toss.
Heave and a miss this time. But it misses the bat and stumps as well.
Naseem Shah is the last man in.

OUT! 9 down and Australia are just a wicket away. Back of a length delivery on middle, Shaheen looks to mow it to over mid-wicket but mistimes it. It lobs towards short cover where Cummins takes the easiest of the catches.
Almost dragged it on the stumps. Full and wide outside off, Shaheen looks to drive but the ball takes the inside edge onto the pads.
Bouncer and around off, Shaheen sways away from the line of the delivery.
Good length ball around off, Shaheen blocks it off the front foot.
Fuller and outside off, Imran pushes at it to get beaten.

Shortish length, aimed at the body. Imran looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the body and then it goes to Labuschagne at short leg. He appeals but not sure for why. Nothing from the umpire.
Back of a length ball on middle, Shaheen pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Two balls to survive for Imran.
Full ball but down the leg side. Shaheen flicks but misses.
On the pads again, Shahenn looks to flick but misses again. The ball goes to short leg.
Pull and a miss! Bouncer and on middle, Shaheen goes for the pull but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Imran looks to turn it towards the leg side but gets hit on the pads. The ball goes towards fine leg but Afridi denies the run.
Good length ball on middle, this time Afridi nudges it towards short fine leg for a single.
Beaten! In the channel outside off, Afridi pokes and misses.

FOUR! That flies off the outside edge. Shortish length ball on middle, Afridi looks to mow it towards mid-wicket but the ball takes the outside edge and flies to the third man fence. 11 more runs and Australia will have to bat again.
On the pads, Imran guides it towards fine leg for a single.
Imran Khan jr is in at 10.

OUT! Pakistan are 8 down now. A nice little cameo comes to an end. A fuller ball on middle, Shah looks to flick but the ball takes the leading edge and balloons towards mid off. Wade at covers runs across from covers and takes a nice catch diving forward. Australia just 2 wickets away.
Fuller and outside off, Shaheen looks to block but ball takes outside edge and goes towards third slip.
FOUR BYES! Did that hit the crack again? It is a shortish length on middle, Afridi ducks under it. Paine though leaps high in the air to pouch but it still goes over the head of Paine.
On the body this time! Shortish length around middle, Shaheen looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the body.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.

FOUR LEG BYES! This time diving Paine cannot save it. Good length ball down the leg side. Shaheen looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. It goes wide of the keeper. Paine dives to his right to save but he cannot stop that from going to the fine leg fence.
FOUR! Wow! Shaheen into the act now. Low full toss on the pads. Shaheen whips it to the deep mid-wicket fence.
THE SECOND NEW BALL IS TAKEN and the king of swing gets the first use of it. Mitchell Starc is back. 14-1-64-2 so far.
Outside off, a play and a miss to end the over.
FOUR! Nicely played! A short ball outside off, Yasir pulls it through mid-wicket! He moves to 42 from 55 balls.

TOP EDGE, SAFE! A length ball, around middle, Yasir looks to flick but gets a top edge. The ball lobs behind and three men run after it - Tim Paine, Joe Burns from first slip and Steven Smith from second slip. The ball eludes all of those and Paine gets to the ball and parries it behind to Smith who returns the throw. Two runs taken.
Around middle, Yasir hops and defends it down the ground.

This is slipped down the leg side, Afridi lets it pass and the ball keeps on kicking after landing. Paine leaps to his right and parries it to fine leg. Wrings his hand in pain. Finger injuries are always a pain for Tim.
Shaheen Afridi walks in at number 9, replacing Rizwan.

OUT! Caught! Rizwan goes for 95! That is so, so, so, so sad for him. He is distraught. He just looks at the fielder, then his shot and thinks, 'What have I done?' It is difficult to say who spent a longer time at the crease after getting out - Rizwan or Sohail yesterday. A short ball outside off, Rizwan leaps and plays the upper cut but he finds Nathan Lyon at deep backward point! Is the innings defeat still on? 35 more needed for Pakistan to avoid that. End of a quickfire 79-run stand.
Josh Hazlewood returns as well. 18-2-51-1 so far.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.

Where has that hit? A crack? Big leg cutter from Cummins. Lands it on a fuller length outside off and makes Yasir Shah poke at it. But the ball suddenly bounces and kicks off, just about beating the outside edge. Now, an alert Tim Paine senses that Yasir is outside the crease and fires a throw at the striker's end. There is an appeal for the run out but the umpire is not interested.
Full and straight, Rizwan drives it off the inner half of the bat through mid on. A single taken.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
A bouncer, Yasir ducks.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. Two runs added to the total.

NOT OUT. But had the decision been given out, Rizwan would have reviewed it. Because he did not hit it in the first place. A full ball, around middle, Rizwan gets across and looks to paddle. Now, the ball goes off something and two people go for the catch - Steven Smith from first slip and Marnus Labuschagne from short leg. Both dive and almost have a nasty collision but avert it. The South African pouches it and then claims the catch, celebrating as well. Umpire Kettleborough checks with Illingworth about the carry and then sends it upstairs, with the soft signal as OUT. Replays are too inconclusive with a big part of the ball touching the ground. But the replays then show the ball not hitting the bat or glove. Snickometer confirms.

Umpire's review for a fair catch! Has Marnus Labuschagne taken a blinder? The sweep shot has produced a top edge off Rizwan and Labuschagne is claiming the catch. But replays show that while taking the catch, the ball just touched the ground. This stand goes on...
Down the leg side, Yasir gets across and nudges it through fine leg for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, Yasir looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge which flies towards the vacant silly point region.
300 UP FOR PAKISTAN! Wow. Take a bow. From 25/3 and 94/5, did not think we would have expected this. Around off, punched uppishly, but well past the bowler down to long on for a single.
Full and outside off, hint of reverse, Yasir looks to defend but gets a bit of an inside edge down the pitch.
Full and around off, pushed wide of mid on for a quick single.
Full and just around off, solidly defended.
Full and around off, pushed through mid on for a quick single.
Around off, solidly defended.

FOUR! Control? Sure! Yasir is in control. Full control. Loosener from Cummins, a half volley on the pads, Yasir just flicks it nonchalantly through square leg! He moves to 33 from 39 balls. The stand is worth 71 from 74 balls.

4 overs left for the second new ball. Paine has gone back to Pat Cummins. 19-6-61-2 so far. Probably because the last 3 overs have gone for 17. The skipper will be hoping for a breakthrough. If not, then at least some control.
Fired in outside off, Rizwan backs away to cut, perhaps but then lets it pass.
Nicely flighted outside off, Shah is early into his walking drive and slices it behind point. A run taken.
Full again, pressed towards cover for a single. Rizwan moves to 90 now.
Full and around off, Rizwan comes down the track and pushes it back to Lyon who mimes a throw back.
Short and outside off, cut through the covers for a couple. The deficit is now 49.
Full and outside off, Rizwan lunges to defend but misses.
That is a bad ball. Short and outside off, Rizwan rocks back and cuts it to sweeper cover for one.

EDGED, WIDE! Exactly what Paine and Labuschagne were hoping for. The shot and the edge. But does not go to hand. Floated outside off, Rizwan reaches out to drive but the ball spins away and takes the outside edge. However, it is wide of Joe Burns at short third man and races to his left. A couple taken.
Outside off, punched towards cover for a run.
Full and around middle, pushed down to long off for a single.
Landed outside off, turning away, left alone.
A little bit of bait thrown up outside off, Rizwan reaches out and drives it straight to shot extra cover.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off, Shah gets across and looks to work it through the leg side but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads. Does not carry to short leg.
FOUR! SPANKED! The deficit is down to 56 now! Boy, we might well see Australia bat  again. Full and around off, Yasir gets down and mows the slog sweep through mid-wicket!
Landed outside off, punched through the covers but straight to the fielder.
Outside off, punched off the back foot.

FOUR! Good thinking. 7 overs to the second new ball, so attack this soft old cherry. The deficit is now 60. Full and around middle, Yasir comes down the track and hammers it wide of mid on for a boundary! He move to 23 now, from just 31 balls.
Nathan Lyon it will be from the other end. 18-3-58-1 so far.

FOUR! 50-RUN STAND IS UP! More frustration for the Aussies. They would have believed that it would not be hard work to wrap things up post the Babar dismissal but Yasir Shah is ensuring that a collapse is not on the cards. Full and outside leg, Rizwan gets down and sweeps it behind square leg. He moves to 83 now.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on for another single.
Pushed through, around off, MR just blocks it towards the off side for one more. The deficit is now 69.
Excellent running. Thrown up outside off, Yasir leans and drives it wide of cover for a quick run.
That is a freebie. A high full toss, Rizwan gets down and mows it via a pull to deep mid-wicket. Just a single.
Full and around leg, watchfully pushed down the track back to the bowler.

The Australian bowlers are out in the middle for the final time on the day. Can this be the final time in the game as well? Well, Mohammad Rizwan and Yasir Shah too walk out and would want to make sure that does not happen. Marnus Labuschagne will continue bowling post Tea.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

Now, now, now. We have a final session on Day 4. Who would have thought that? Well, the superb 132-run stand between Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan have ensured this session. While Azam has gone back after his maiden Test ton against the Aussies, Rizwan is looking solid out in the middle. He along with Yasir Shah has added 42 runs and would want the stand going as big as they can. Lyon managed the prized scalp of Azam in the session after the latter played a classy knock of 104. Now, how long these two batters can keep the association going? Will they be able to take the game into the fifth day? Join us for the final session of the day to find out.
Another solid defense from Shah to this ball on off. TEA ON DAY 4.
This is quicker one and off, Yasir defends it out.
On middle, Shah keeps it out.
Nicely bowled! Looped up outside off, Shah looks to sweep but he is early in the shot. He manages a bottom edge which drops it near the silly point fielder.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and around off, Shah sweeps but finds square leg.
Another short ball and this time Shah taps it through point for a single.
Shortish length around off, Rizwan taps it towards deep point for a single.
FOUR! This is sweetly timed. Shortish length on middle, Rizwan goes on the back foot and hammers it wide of mid on. Starc looks to chase the ball down but eventually loses the race.
Shortish and outside off, Shah reaches out and pushes it towards mid off for a single.

Top edge this time! This is mostly the last over before Lunch. Wonder why he is going after the ball. Another ball which is slightly short. Shah goes for the massive pull again but this time manages a top edge which goes away from the mid on fielder. A couple of runs taken.
FOUR! A long hop this one. Short and around off, Yasir hammers is to the mid-wicket fence.
Marnus Labuschagne to bowl. 2-0-12-0 so far.
Flighted and on off, Shah once again lunges forward and pushes it towards point for a single.
Fullish and around middle, Rizwan pushes it towards long on for a single.
Full and on middle, Shah sweeps it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Around off, Shah comes forward and blocks it right of the silly point fielder.

Nicely bowled! The inside edge there saved him. Lyon gives this ball a lot of air and around off, Rizwan once again ventures out of the crease and looks to flick but manages a thick inside edge which goes to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Smashed through the covers. Full and around off, Rizwan skips down the track and creams it through the covers.
Nathan Lyon to bowl now.
Full and outside off, Shah digs it out towards point.
Good length again and just outside off, Yasir blocks it out.
Length around off, Rizwan taps it towards point for a quick run.
Full and on middle, Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler who looks to field but misses. It goes to mid on and no runs can be taken.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short and on middle, Rizwan looks to pull but it hits the splice of the bat and drops on the pitch.
FOUR BYES! This a poor ball, way down the leg side. Paine could've done nothing as it races to the fine leg fence. Shah though went for the flick but it kept going away.
On the pads, Rizwan tucks it towards backward square leg for a single.

Good combination fielding. Outside off, on a length, Rizwan punches this through the covers. Nathan Lyon chases it from point and David Warner gets across from sweeper cover. Gary gets to it first, slides and then parries it to Warner. Two runs taken. Deliberately, one feels. Rizwan will not want to expose to the tail-ender specialist.
Shortish and around off, Rizwan stands tall and blocks it towards cover.
On the pads, Yasir nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Ouch! Starc steams in from around the wicket and bowls an incoming ball into the batter. Shah hangs his bat to defend but misses to get hit on the stomach.
Slightly short on middle, Shah pulls it towards square leg for a single.
Around off, Shah keeps it out by coming forward.
Bouncer now! Typical fast bowler's response. Shah though does really well to sway away from the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Guided away! Slightly shortish and outside off. Shah just guides it through point and gully and into the third man fence.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Huge appeal for LBW! Looks really close. No, an inside edge. Excellent decision from the umpire there. Good length ball, angled into the batter. Shah looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad. Loud loud appeal from the Australians but the umpire is unmoved. Replays show a big deflection off the bat and then on the pads.
Hazlewood returns.
On the pads, Shah looks to turn it towards the leg side. But he is hit on the pads. A muted appeal from the bowler but nothing from the umpire.

Fullish and on off, Rizwan pushes it towards cover and takes off for a single. Wade there picks the ball and fires a throw at the non-striker's end but misses. Marnus Labuschagne does well to back it up. Replays roll in and show that the batter was short there.
Bouncer on middle from Starc. Rizwan ducks under it.
On the pads, Yasir flicks it towards fine leg and takes a run to get off the mark.
Back of a length and around off, Shah keeps it out.
Good length ball down the leg side. Yasir looks to tickle it fine but misses.
Mitchell Starc replaces Lyon. Surprising. Lyon got a wicket in the last over.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan goes back and cuts it through point and into the third man fence. Lyon from point chases it but the ball wins the race.
Just short of the diving cover fielder. Full and outside off. Rizwan reaches out and drives it uppishly. Lucky that it did not carry to the fielder.
Shortish and around off. Rizwan taps it onto the pitch.
Three in a row! Cummins bangs short on middle. Rizwan ducks again.
And another one. This is on middle though but too high. Rizwan once again ducks.
Bouncer down the leg side from Cummins. He bowled a few last over as well but the line has not been right. Rizwan easily ducks under it.
Yasir Shah walks in next.

OUT! Lyon strikes and the big fish is out of here. A superb knock from Azam comes to an end. The 132-run stand is broken. This is slightly quicker and shortish in length. Azam goes back to punch it off the back foot but only manages a faint tickle back to Paine. He gobbles it nicely and appeals. The umpire raises his finger and Babar walks off. He shows his bat to the crowd as he gets a massive applause. Pakistan might still lose this by an innings but it has an excellent fight shown by Babar and Rizwan. The deficit is now 114.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
He eases a single through mid on now.
Flighted and around off, Rizwan comes forward and keeps it out.
Full and outside off, Azam drives it wide of the mid off fielder and takes a single.
On middle, Babar pushes it back to the bowler by venturing out of the crease. Lyon picks the ball and throws at the striker's end but misses.
Another bouncer! This time Rizwan ducks under it.

Cries of catch but it is in the gap. Excellent fielding from Starc from fine leg to save a couple of runs for his side. Short ball on middle, Rizwan takes on the challenge and goes for the pull. He top edges it high in the air. It drops between the fine leg fielder and the deep mid-wicket fielder. Starc runs across his left from fine leg and slides to push the ball back in and save a couple of runs.
Bouncer down the leg side. Rizwan has no business with it.
Shortish length ball around off, Rizwan pushes it towards cover.
Bouncer way over the head of Rizwan.
Good length ball angled in, Azam tucks it towards fine leg to take an easy single.
Turn and bounce there. Slightly shortish ball, Rizwan looks to cut moving across on the leg side but misses to put any bat on ball.
On middle, Babar this time tucks it through mid on for a single.
Another flighted ball around off, Babar once again comes forward and defends.
Flighted and around off, tapped towards the off side coming forward.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, pushed to cover.
What was that? Rizwan would not want to get out in this fashion. A short ball on middle, he first wants to duck but then flashes his bat to upper cut. Makes no connection. Very risky shot that one.
Full and wide outside off, Rizwan reaches out and drives it through the covers. Wade chases it down to keep it to a couple.
Shortish and around off, Rizwan taps it towards point.
On off, Rizwan keeps it out.

Now then, what happened on 58.6? The replays are shown now. We all felt that there was an inside edge. However, the replays now show that the ball hit the pad first, then the bat! And Ball Tracker shows it to be plumb!
Bouncer on middle. Rizwan has no problem swaying away from it.
On middle and leg, Azam flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
This is punched towards cover.
Around off, punched towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and outside off, watchfully defended.

FOUR! 'CATCH!' is the call from Paine. But the ball has sailed over. Maiden Test Fifty for Rizwan. Full and outside off, Rizwan gets down and looks to play the sweep but there is extra bounce on that. Takes the top edge and short fine leg runs back while deep mid-wicket run across. But the ball lands nowhere close to them and scurries to the fine leg fence.

Drinks! The battle from Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan continues and they are keeping the Australian bowlers at bay. Azam has just completed his second Test ton while Rizwan is just two short of his half ton. They will want to continue batting and take the game as deep as possible. They have done it in the first hour of the session. Can they continue doing so in the second hour of the session? Meanwhile, Lyon returns with a change of end.
Fullish ball, swinging in. Azam looks to flick but manages a thick inside edge on the pads.
Good length ball angled into him, Azam tucks it towards mid on.

FOUR! There is the hundred. Second in Tests which means so much for him. He has stood out in the middle amidst the chaos happening at the other end. He gets there with a superb drive through the covers to this good length ball outside off. He is not done yet and would want to convert this one into the massive one.
Another bouncer! This is on middle and off. Azam does well to sway away from it.
Bouncer one middle, Azam ducks under it.
FOUR! Dispatched. 4 away from his first Test ton against Australia. A bouncer on middle, Azam pulls it by rolling his wrists on this one. It races to the mid-wicket fence.
Pat Cummins into the attack. 15-6-43-2 are his figures so far.
Gets this bouncer right does Starc. Rizwan though once again stands tall and taps it onto the pitch.
Bouncer down the leg side. Rizwan has no problems ducking under it.
Play and a miss this time! shortish length again form Starc. Rizwan this time looks to upper cut it but misses.
Shortish length on middle, Rizwan keeps it out.

FOUR! Beautifully done! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan rides on the bounce and slams it over the point region and into the fence. They check if it has gone over the ropes but not really, just bounces inside.
Good length ball on the pads, Rizwan defends it out nicely.
On the pads, Babar turns it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Superbly driven off the back foot. Poor length this one. Short and wide, Azam goes back and slams it through covers for a boundary. Moves into the 90s.

On middle, Babar comes down the track to and defends. There is a muted appeal for for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Head at short mid-wicket though makes an extended appeal, makes no difference to the umpire though.
Quicker one and a shortish length, Babar tucks it towards short fine leg.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Beaten! Beautifully bowled! This is again slightly shortish length which pitches on middle and shapes away from the poke of Rizwan.
This time a superb punch from Babar and on the off side. Slightly shortish ball outside off, Azam crunches it past the diving cover fielder.

Nicely punched. Slightly shortish length ball, Rizwan stays on the back foot and punches it through mid-wicket. Hazlewood from that position hares at the ball, slider and stops and throws it back to the keeper. Three runs taken.
Another short ball but this is way outside off, Rizwan drops his wrists and lets it be.
Shortish length ball on middle, Babar hops and turns it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated delivery on off, Rizwan defends it out.
Tossed up delivery on off, Rizwan blocks it well.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rizwan defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Cracking shot. Short delivery on off, Rizwan makes room and cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Rizwan drives it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Babar comes down the track and drives it to long on. The batsmen take a single.
Muted appeal for caught behind by the wicket keeper and the slip cordon. Starc shows no interest though. Shortish ball around off, Rizwan swivels and pull but misses out to connect.
Bouncer way over the head of the batter and even keeper who leaps high to pouch it over his head.
Short delivery on off, Rizwan blocks it well.
Short and outside off, Rizwan cuts it to point where Nathan Lyon dives to his left and makes a fine stop.
On a length and outside off, Azam taps it towards point. The batsmen take a single.

NOT OUT! Babar survives a close call. That looked plumb to the naked eyes. This pitches around off and comes back in sharply. Babar looks to work/flick on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads. Hazlewood appeals along with Paine and entire slip cordon. Not out says the umpire there. Paine just thinks and thinks and then takes the review. Let us see what the replays show. Hot Spot first, nothing on it. Time for Snicko, no deflection there. Here comes the Ball Tracker. Just clipping the leg stump, so, umpire's call it will be. This can be termed a unlucky one for the bowling side or maybe not because had the umpire given Babar out, one would feel that the batter was unlucky there. Australia retain the review but fail to send Babar packing, for now.

A LBW appeal turned down against Babar Azam. Paine  has taken it upstairs after consulting his bowler. Looks really close this one. Here comes Hot Spot, nothing on it. Nothing on Snicko either. Now, the Ball Tracker, hitting the top of leg, just top of leg so, umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Babar stays. But an excellent review this one.
Fullish and on off, Rizwan keeps it out coming forward.
FIVE WIDES! Wayward delivery this one. Short of length down the leg side. It pitches and keeps going away from diving Pant. It races to the fine leg fence and the umpire calls it wide.

On a good length on off, Rizwan taps it towards covers and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Dispatched! Short of a length delivery, Rizwan pulls it through square leg for a boundary.

Full delivery on middle, Babar drives it straight back towards the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Rizwan defends it off the back foot.

Outside off, left alone.
Played with soft hands there. Length delivery on off, Rizwan looks to push it towards the point region but it takes the outside edge and goes towards gully on the bounce.
Fuller and on off, Rizwan comes forward and blocks it.

Slightly shortish ball around off, Rizwan guides it through the gully region. Warner chases the ball down and makes a tumbling stop. Lyon is there to assist him as he picks the ball and send it back to the keeper. A couple of runs taken.
Fullish and on off. Babar keeps it out. 5 from the over.

Full delivery on middle, Rizwan flicks it through square leg. The batsmen take a single.

Good length delivery on off, Azam keeps it out.
